nexpress.com |publisher=Indian Express |accessdate=17 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911002514/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/boman-irani-on-sanjay-dutt-biopic-they-are-certain-stories-only-rajkumar-hirani-can-tell-4739977/ |archivedate=11 September 2017  }}</ref>\n*[[Sayaji Shinde]] as Bandu Dada\n*[[Piyush Mishra]] as D.N. Tripathi, a screenwriter.\n*Aditi Gautam as [[Priya Dutt]], Sanju's sister<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roychoudhury |first1=Shibaji |title=Sanju: This actress hated playing Ranbir Kapoor's sister in the Rajkumar Hirani film, here's why |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/sanju-this-actress-hated-playing-ranbir-kapoor-s-sister-in-the-rajkumar-hirani-film-here-s-why/246240 |website=timesnownews.com |publisher=Times Now |accessdate=26 June 2018 |date=26 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627115055/https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/sanju-this-actress-hated-playing-ranbir-kapoor-s-sister-in-the-rajkumar-hirani-film-here-s-why/246240 |archivedate=27 June 2018  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Correspondent |first1=HT |title=Here is the first look of Aditi Gautam as Priya Dutt in Sanju. See pic |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/here-is-the-first-look-of-aditi-gautam-as-priya-dutt-in-sanju-see-pic/story-QUyA4wT8EVCNI4RkIdRLoL.html |website=hindustantimes.com |publisher=Hindustan Times |accessdate=26 June 2018 |date=26 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626091247/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/here-is-the-first-look-of-aditi-gautam-as-priya-dutt-in-sanju-see-pic/story-QUyA4wT8EVCNI4RkIdRLoL.html |archivedate=26 June 2018  }}</ref>\n**[[Ashnoor Kaur]] as young [[Priya Dutt]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju: Who's playing who in Sanjay Dutt biopic? |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-whos-playing-sanjay-dutt-biopic-1502654481.html |website=The Statesman |accessdate=8 July 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Yuri Suri]] as Hawant Singh, Sanju's lawyer\n*[[Ashwin Mushran]] as an event manager\n*[[Anjan Srivastav]] as a minister\n*[[Prakash Belawadi]] as a newspaper editor\n*[[Mahesh Manjrekar]] as himself (cameo)\n*[[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]] as herself (cameo)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tabu-to-do-a-cameo-role-in-sanjay-dutt-biopic-will-play-herself-in-the-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-328025.html|title=Tabu To Do A Cameo Role In Sanjay Dutt Biopic, Will Play Herself In The Ranbir Kapoor Starrer|publisher=The Times of India|date=17 August 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821015959/http://www.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tabu-to-do-a-cameo-role-in-sanjay-dutt-biopic-will-play-herself-in-the-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-328025.html|archivedate=21 August 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Arshad Warsi]] as Circuit (cameo, archive footage of [[Munnabhai M.B.B.S.]])\n*[[Anil Mange|Anil Charanjeet]] as singer in the song \"Main Badiya Tu Bhi Badiya\" (special appearance)<ref>{{cite news |title=Sanju song Badhiya |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/030618/sanju-song-badhiya-interchange-of-gender-for-ranbir-and-sonam.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180611192041/https://deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/030618/sanju-song-badhiya-interchange-of-gender-for-ranbir-and-sonam.html |archivedate=11 June 2018  }}</ref>\n*[[Sanjay Dutt]] as himself (end credits)<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web |last1=Shiksha |first1=Shruti |title=Sanju: Sanjay Dutt's Role In Ranbir Kapoor's Film Revealed. Details Here |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/sanju-sanjay-dutts-role-in-ranbir-kapoors-film-revealed-details-here-1870287 |website=ndtv.com |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=21 June 2018 |date=20 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620082150/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/sanju-sanjay-dutts-role-in-ranbir-kapoors-film-revealed-details-here-1870287 |archivedate=20 June 2018  }}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\n[[File:Rajkumar Hirani 2014.jpg|thumb|upright|Hirani ''(pictured in 2014)'']]\nDirector [[Rajkumar Hirani]] was first prompted to create a film based on [[Sanjay Dutt]]'s life by the latter's wife [[Manyata Dutt]] in a casual conversation, an offer he refused, reasoning that \"Sanju\u2019s world is very different from my world\".<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web |last1=Sinha |first1=Seema |title=Rajkumar Hirani on why Ranbir Kapoor was his first choice for Sanju: 'He is a fantastic actor and open to criticism' |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/rajkumar-hirani-on-why-ranbir-kapoor-was-his-first-choice-for-sanju-he-is-a-fantastic-actor-and-open-to-criticism-4587951.html |website=first-post.com |accessdate=25 June 2018 |date=25 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626030130/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/rajkumar-hirani-on-why-ranbir-kapoor-was-his-first-choice-for-sanju-he-is-a-fantastic-actor-and-open-to-criticism-4587951.html |archivedate=26 June 2018  }}</ref> In an interview with ''[[Daily News & Analysis]]'', Hirani revealed what eventually prompted him to create a film based on Sanjay Dutt's life: \"He was lonely. Manyata (I think) was in hospital and he used to go there (sometimes) and then come home to an empty house. So, he was just venting, speaking straight from the heart. And, he started giving me anecdotes that were just gems for a filmmaker\". In regards to gaining resources in constructing the film, Hirani said, \"...we sat for a crazy amount of time and recorded everything ... I also met others who knew him&nbsp;\u2014 journalists, cops, relatives and friends. I felt there was a movie that should be told.\"<ref name=\"iyer1\" /> In an interview with DNA After Hrs, Hirani confirmed that the film was named ''Sanju'' after a lot of deliberation as [[Nargis]], Sanjay's mother, used to call him \u2018Sanju\u2019.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sanjay Shah|first1=Karan|title=It's Official! Ranbir Kapoor's Sanjay Dutt biopic has been titled Sanju and Rajkumar Hirani reveals why|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/ranbir-kapoors-sanjay-dutt-biopic-has-been-titled-sanju-and-rajkumar-hirani-reveals-why/|website=Bollywoodlife.com|publisher=Bollywoodlife.com|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508054218/http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/ranbir-kapoors-sanjay-dutt-biopic-has-been-titled-sanju-and-rajkumar-hirani-reveals-why/|archivedate=8 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nProducer [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]] was not a part of the project when Hirani initially approached him to produce the film. At first, Chopra was of the opinion that \"it was hogwash... but when we started researching all that he\u2019s said \u2014 from the 308 girlfriends he had to how he begged on the streets of US for the money to buy a bus ticket \u2014 we realised that everything he had told us was true!\".<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web |last1=Roy |first1=Priyanka |title=Ranbir Kapoor has become Sanjay Dutt in swagger and soul \u2014 Vidhu Vinod Chopra |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/ranbir-kapoor-has-become-sanjay-dutt-in-swagger-and-soul-vidhu-vinod-238799?ref=hm-new-stry |website=telegraphindia.com |publisher=Telegraph India |accessdate=19 June 2018 |date=19 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620001929/https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/ranbir-kapoor-has-become-sanjay-dutt-in-swagger-and-soul-vidhu-vinod-238799?ref=hm-new-stry |archivedate=20 June 2018  }}</ref> Hirani had a pre-condition with Dutt that if the latter requested to change any lines or scenes, he \"would not make it\", upon which Dutt allowed Hirani to make the film in his accord.<ref>{{cite web |title=REVEALED: Rajkumar Hirani's precondition before he made the Sanjay Dutt biopic Sanju |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/revealed-rajkumar-hiranis-precondition-made-sanjay-dutt-biopic-sanju/ |website=bollywoodhungama.com |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=22 May 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627115055/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/revealed-rajkumar-hiranis-precondition-made-sanjay-dutt-biopic-sanju/ |archivedate=27 June 2018  }}</ref> He was okay with Hirani not glorifying him in the film.<ref name=\"iyer1\" /> Hirani showed aspects of Dutt's life that the public would not have known, such as \"what was happening in the Dutt household when Sanju was accused of the crime? What was his father going through? What was happening with his sisters? How were his friends reacting? Later I met his sisters, Namrata and Priya, brother-in-law Kumar Gaurav and US-based friend Paresh Ghelani.\" Hirani stated, \"The film is not about his romance. It has primarily two tracks, one is the gun story and the other is the drugs story and how he fought these two battles.\"<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n\nSpeaking about Dutt's journey, Kapoor revealed in an interview with ''[[Filmfare]]'' that the biopic will reach out to the audience by teaching them something. He stated that \"It will talk about human flaws, the emotional father-son story (between Sanjay and the late Sunil Dutt), his relationship with his best friend, with the women in his life. It's emotional, it's funny, it's sad, it's bittersweet. The youth have a lot to learn from his mistakes.\" He also confirmed that \"it's not a propaganda film\" intending to glorify Dutt.<ref>{{cite web|last1=i|first1=Madhur|title=Dia Mirza On Dutt Biopic: People Who Went On The Sets Thought Ranbir Kapoor Was Sanju Sir|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/news/2018/dia-mirza-on-dutt-biopic-people-who-went-on-the-sets-thought-ranbir-kapoor-was-sanju-sir/articlecontent-pf236622-271001.html|website=filmibeat.com|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref> Kapoor also revealed that for him the hardest aspect of playing the role was to give himself the confidence to go ahead with the project. For him, Sanjay Dutt is \"a flawed but a wonderful person... a pop icon\" and that's why it was scary.Kapoor also stated that there are \"six different phases, six different looks and six different controversies\" in the film.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yount |first1=Stacey |title=Ranbir Kapoor: \"In Sanju, I tried to play him with a lot of respect, dignity and honesty\" |url=https://bollyspice.com/ranbir-kapoor-in-sanju-i-tried-to-play-him-with-a-lot-of-respect-dignity-and-honesty/ |website=bollyspice.com |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628190531/https://bollyspice.com/ranbir-kapoor-in-sanju-i-tried-to-play-him-with-a-lot-of-respect-dignity-and-honesty/ |archivedate=28 June 2018  }}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with [[Rajeev Masand]], Hirani disclosed that the story-telling procedure was \"challenging as it's not a story of an achiever\" as most biopics are based on a heroic personality, yet Dutt is known for his tragedies and losses. He noted that \"you can't really tamper\" and that the main scripting challenge was fitting \"a very anecdotal story in a structured format\". Writer [[Abhijat Joshi]] also revealed that there was no \"deliberate\" attempt to make Dutt's character sympathetic to the audience. Instead the team realised having listened to all the anecdotes conveyed by Dutt that it's a \"very engaging, incredibly fascinating\" story based on a \"conflicted person, a flawed person\" who \"deserved empathy\". Hirani then confirmed that he has \"put out the truth\" which includes \"good things and bad things\".<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web|last1=Masand|first1=Rajeev|title=Office Space: Inside Rajkumar Hirani Films with Rajkumar Hirani|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5fcaCloa6go|website=youtube.com|publisher=Rajeev Masand|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref> In another interview, Hirani also revealed that like his other films, Sanju would also deliver a social message: \"there is the father-son story, a friendship and one is a question mark. For the last one, you\u2019ll have to see the film. Hirani also revealed that he did initially get \"attracted to all the anecdotes [that Dutt was conveying]\" but soon \"realized it was not enough \u2013 we had to be able to string it all together.\" which led him to come to the conclusion that \"people need to know is his gun story [and his drug story], because it is important. If there is no gun story, there is no biopic\" which then in turn formed the \"spine\" of the film.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jamkhandikar |first1=Shilpa |title=I have not given Sanjay Dutt a clean chit in Sanju, says Rajkumar Hirani |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-have-not-given-sanjay-dutt-a-clean-chit-in-sanju-says-rajkumar-hirani/story-QAk2eTOe12X4I76YhIbfJN.html |website=hindustantimes.com |publisher=Hindustan Times |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=27 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627164740/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-have-not-given-sanjay-dutt-a-clean-chit-in-sanju-says-rajkumar-hirani/story-QAk2eTOe12X4I76YhIbfJN.html |archivedate=27 June 2018  }}</ref>\n\nPost the release of the film, both Hirani and Joshi reasoned that Dutt has not been \"whitewashed\" in the film as many critics have openly said so. Instead Hirani questioned \"I want to know what have I whitewashed? I have shown that he had 308 girlfriends, that he was so addicted to drugs, he slept with his friend\u2019s girlfriend. Is this whitewashing?\". Joshi also commented that \"What we are bashing is a certain section which sensationalises things and uses a question mark to make things \u2018chatpata\u2019 (spicy). That has been critiqued, and I am amazed there has been no introspection on that side. No one has even said that it happens.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Rajkumar Hirani on Sanjay Dutt's biopic Sanju: What have I whitewashed? |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/rajkumar-hirani-sanju-what-have-i-whitewashed-422953 |website=pinkvilla.com |accessdate=12 August 2018 |date=12 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\n\nActor [[Ranbir Kapoor]] was Hirani's first choice to play Dutt's character. Hirani stated, \"I first thought of Ranbir and went straight to him and I can tell you, we were right.\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sanju: Ranbir Kapoor's movie trailer to release along with other cast, says Rajkumar Hirani|url=http://laughingcolours.com/sanju-ranbir-kapoors-movie-trailer-to-release-along-with-other-cast-says-rajkumar-hirani-81591/|website=laughingcolours.com|accessdate=25 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526041209/http://laughingcolours.com/sanju-ranbir-kapoors-movie-trailer-to-release-along-with-other-cast-says-rajkumar-hirani-81591/|archivedate=26 May 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He also stated that he thought Kapoor is a fantastic actor and \"at the perfect age.\"<ref name=\"iyer1\" /> He further revealed the similarities and differences between Dutt and Kapoor stating that \"they have lived the life of actors all through. Ranbir is not someone from outside the industry who came here to be a hero. In a sense, it was easier for me to see him as Sanju.\" He also revealed that Ranbir Kapoor worked very hard to get the correct physicality, spending days watching videos \"to strike the right balance\"<ref name=\"iyer1\" /> Initially Kapoor was reluctant to portray the role. However, he agreed once \"he saw the angle of the story\"<ref name=\"iyer1\">{{cite web|last1=Iyer|first1=Meena|title=Rajkumar Hirani on Sanjay Dutt biopic|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/interview-rajkumar-hirani-on-sanjay-dutt-biopic-i-told-sanju-we-won-t-glorify-him-and-he-was-okay-with-it-2607854|website=DNA India|publisher=DNA India|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508112410/http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/interview-rajkumar-hirani-on-sanjay-dutt-biopic-i-told-sanju-we-won-t-glorify-him-and-he-was-okay-with-it-2607854|archivedate=8 May 2018}}</ref> and that the story \"broke certain notions I had about him [Dutt]\". Kapoor also revealed that his initial \"hesitation\" about playing Dutt's role was that he is \"still so relevant today\" and is a \"superstar\" who is \"working in movies today... [and] has lots to achieve and lots to do\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Masand |first1=Rajeev |title=Ranbir Kapoor interview with Rajeev Masand |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5GuBTcqBIJg |website=youtube.com |publisher=Rajeev Masand |accessdate=16 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nChopra was also reluctant to produce the film with Kapoor in the lead role, as he believed [[Ranveer Singh]] would've been a better fit to Dutt's part by having the \"flamboyance, the emotional depth as well as the ability to change himself completely to play Sanjay Dutt.\". Chopra however, \"had to kind of eat [his] words\" once shooting began and he witnessed Kapoor's capabilities playing Dutt.<ref name=\"auto3\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Gaikwad |first1=Pramod |title=Not Ranbir but Ranveer Singh could play Sanjay Dutt's role much better: Vidhu Vinod Chopra |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/not-ranbir-ranveer-singh-could-play-sanjay-dutts-role-much-better-vidhu-vinod-chopra-772569 |website=ibtimes.co.in |publisher=International Business Times |accessdate=24 June 2018 |date=20 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625021608/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/not-ranbir-ranveer-singh-could-play-sanjay-dutts-role-much-better-vidhu-vinod-chopra-772569 |archivedate=25 June 2018  }}</ref> Kapoor responded to Chopra's comments by stating that he was \"very happy\" to be a part of the film as it came at a time where \"he was really in need of inspiration.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sabharwal |first1=Mehak |title=Ranbir Kapoor opens up about Ranveer Singh being Vidhu Vinod Chopra's first choice for Sanju |url=http://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/ranbir-kapoor-opens-up-about-ranveer-singh-being-vidhu-vinod-chopras-first-choice-for-sanju/244494 |website=timesnownews.com |publisher=Times Now |accessdate=24 June 2018 |format=web |date=22 June 2018}}</ref> Like Kapoor, Koirala was also \"scepital\" about playing a mother to Kapoor due to the fear of being \"typecast.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Manisha Koirala was sceptical about playing Nargis |url=http://www.asianage.com/entertainment/bollywood/240618/manisha-koirala-was-sceptical-about-playing-nargis.html |website=asianage.com |accessdate=24 June 2018 |date=24 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180624014049/http://www.asianage.com/entertainment/bollywood/240618/manisha-koirala-was-sceptical-about-playing-nargis.html |archivedate=24 June 2018  }}</ref>\n\n[[Aamir Khan]] was also approached to play the role of Dutt's father, [[Sunil Dutt]]. However, the role was turned down as Khan was already playing the role of a father at that time in [[Dangal (film)|Dangal]]. Khan had also stated that he wished to have played Dutt's role instead as his \"role is so wonderful that it won my heart... so don\u2019t offer me any other role as I won\u2019t be able to do it\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Staff|first1=JKR|title=Aamir Khan reveals why he refused to act in Sanju|url=http://www.jantakareporter.com/india/aamir-khan-reveals-why-he-refused-to-act-in-sanju/187782/|website=jantakarereporter.com|accessdate=25 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526041912/http://www.jantakareporter.com/india/aamir-khan-reveals-why-he-refused-to-act-in-sanju/187782/|archivedate=26 May 2018}}</ref> The role was then passed onto actor [[Paresh Rawal]] who stated that his character is \"human\" and \"doesn't have a set mannerism, idiosyncrasy\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sharma|first1=Priyanka|title=Paresh Rawal on Sanjay Dutt biopic: It is primarily a father-son story|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/paresh-rawal-on-sanjay-dutt-biopic-it-is-primarily-a-father-son-story-4744166/|website=indianexpress.com|accessdate=25 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170814040006/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/paresh-rawal-on-sanjay-dutt-biopic-it-is-primarily-a-father-son-story-4744166/|archivedate=14 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nInitial reports suggested that actress [[Anushka Sharma]] was approached to play the character of one of Dutt's girlfriends, and then a rumoured journalist. However, Sharma denied these claims by stating that \"my character is the only fictional character in the film\" and \"is not based on any living person\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Misra|first1=Tishya|title=Post Vacation, Anushka Sharma Shoots For Sanjay Dutt Biopic In New York|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/post-vacation-anushka-sharma-shoots-for-sanjay-dutt-biopic-in-new-york-1726364|website=ndtv.com|accessdate=25 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526112848/https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/post-vacation-anushka-sharma-shoots-for-sanjay-dutt-biopic-in-new-york-1726364|archivedate=26 May 2018}}</ref> At the trailer launch, Hirani stated that Sharma plays a biographer from London who comes to India, and in turn plays a \"mix\" of himself and [[Abhijat Joshi]].<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nIt was also reportedly initially that [[Sonam Kapoor]] would be playing the character of [[Tina Munim]].<ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|last1=Jalan|first1=Shivangi|title=Sanju new poster: Sonam Kapoor's crackling chemistry with Ranbir Kapoor is a page out of Sanjay Dutt's life|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-poster-sonam-kapoor-ranbir-kapoor-5190512/|website=Indian Express|publisher=Indian Express|accessdate=25 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526021848/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-poster-sonam-kapoor-ranbir-kapoor-5190512/|archivedate=26 May 2018}}</ref> Kapoor, however refuted these rumours and stated that \"I have a small but important part in the movie. It's not what everyone is thinking. I am not playing an actress.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Prabhu|first1=Madhuri|title=Sanju: Ranbir Kapoor- Sonam Kapoor's Playful Vibes Gives A Hint Of Sanjay Dutt's Crazy Love Life!|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/news/2018/sanju-ranbir-kapoor-sonam-kapoor-playful-vibes-gives-a-hint-of-sanjay-dutt-crazy-love-life/articlecontent-pf251623-273945.html|website=filmibeat.com|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref> Though, Hirani confirmed that Kapoor is indeed playing the role of \"a girlfriend\".<ref name=\"auto4\"/>\n\nSpeaking on his role, [[Vicky Kaushal]] revealed that his character is an \"amalgamation of three or four other friends\" of Dutt and is thus \"fictionalized\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=NS |first1=IA |title=Vicky Kaushal: I went through a huge physical transformation for Sanju |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vicky-kaushal-i-went-through-a-huge-physical-transformation-for-sanju-5221081/ |website=indianexpress.com |publisher=Indian Express |accessdate=18 June 2018 |date=17 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618002717/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vicky-kaushal-i-went-through-a-huge-physical-transformation-for-sanju-5221081/ |archivedate=18 June 2018  }}</ref> Whilst [[Karishma Tanna]]'s role is yet unknown, Tanna revealed that it had been intended by Hirani and the rest of the team to keep her role a surprise and that Hirani \"made it clear to [her] that [her] role would create a lot of speculation\" as it is \"exactly what [they] had anticipated.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Farzeen |first1=Sana |title=Is Karishma Tanna playing Madhuri Dixit in Sanju? Here's what the TV actor has to say |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/karishma-tanna-on-her-role-in-sanju-5210008/ |website=indianexpress.com |publisher=Indian Express |accessdate=25 June 2018 |date=25 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625111246/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/karishma-tanna-on-her-role-in-sanju-5210008/ |archivedate=25 June 2018  }}</ref> [[Boman Irani]] expressed that he was cast as Hirani wanted him to do a special appearance. Speaking about his character, Irani stated that \"it's not a known character but may have existed\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sharma |first1=Dipti |title=Boman Irani on Sanjay Dutt biopic: There are certain stories only Rajkumar Hirani can tell |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/boman-irani-on-sanjay-dutt-biopic-they-are-certain-stories-only-rajkumar-hirani-can-tell-4739977/ |website=indianexpress.com |publisher=Indian Express |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=7 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Characters ===\n\n[[Ranbir Kapoor]] requested and was given a month's break between every phase to complete his transformation into Dutt. Speaking about it at the teaser launch of the film, he stated that it was hard for him to look like the muscular Dutt as Kapoor has a thinner frame. \"...there was a lot of team effort behind this. A year before that we did a lot of prep and screen tests...\"<ref name=\"teaser1\">{{cite web|last1=Mathur|first1=Kajol|title=Ranbir Kapoor's Sanju teaser crosses 30 million on YouTube in 48 hours|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/ranbir-kapoors-sanju-teaser-crosses-30-million-on-youtube-in-48-hours-27902.html|website=Filmfare.com|publisher=Filmfare|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508121454/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/ranbir-kapoors-sanju-teaser-crosses-30-million-on-youtube-in-48-hours-27902.html|archivedate=8 May 2018}}</ref> In regards to Kapoor's transformation, father [[Rishi Kapoor]] revealed that Ranbir \"took 6\u20137 weeks to get each of his different looks\"<ref>{{cite web|title=If Ranbir's one film like Jagga Jassos flops he has no work, Rishi Kapoor reveals|url=https://deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/270418/ranbir-one-film-jagga-jasoos-flops-he-has-no-work-rishi-kapoor-reveal.html|website=DecchanChronicle.com|publisher=Deccan Chronicle|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180507012950/https://deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/270418/ranbir-one-film-jagga-jasoos-flops-he-has-no-work-rishi-kapoor-reveal.html|archivedate=7 May 2018}}</ref> In an interview, prosthetic artist, Dr Suresh Murkey said that he used prosthetics to make Ranbir Kapoor's face and age resemble Dutt's.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dedhia|first1=Sonil|title=Gave Ranbir Kapoor Puffy Eyes To Resemble Sanjay Dutt|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/gave-ranbir-kapoor-puffy-eyes-to-resemble-sanjay-dutt/19386179|website=mid-day.com|publisher=mid-day.com|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508054027/https://www.mid-day.com/articles/gave-ranbir-kapoor-puffy-eyes-to-resemble-sanjay-dutt/19386179|archivedate=8 May 2018}}</ref> Kapoor further commented that he would be sitting for hair and makeup for six hours and \"tests after tests [they] kept failing\". It was also difficult to develop Dutt's ageing process as \"because of alcohol,  his face had gotten puffy and his chin had kind of come down.\" Kapoor however, was also \"very clear that if we cannot achieve his look, we will not make the film\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chauhan |first1=Soumya |title=Sanju: From having 8 meals a day to sitting 6 hours on makeup chair everyday, watch how Ranbir Kapoor became Sanjay Dutt |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-sanju-from-having-8-meals-a-day-to-sitting-6-hours-on-makeup-chair-everyday-watch-how-ranbir-kapoor-became-sanjay-dutt-2633860 |website=dnaindia.com |publisher=DNA India |accessdate=6 July 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nMirza also opened up on Kapoor's role stating that \"he would be the first to reach the location because he would need five, six hours to do prosthetic make-up to play the older part.\" She also spoke about the uncanny resemblance of Kapoor as Dutt as a consequence of prosthetics revealing that \"people who went on the sets thought Ranbir was Sanju sir.<ref>{{cite web|last1=i|first1=Madhur|title=Dia Mirza On Dutt Biopic: People Who Went On The Sets Thought Ranbir Kapoor Was Sanju Sir|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/news/2018/dia-mirza-on-dutt-biopic-people-who-went-on-the-sets-thought-ranbir-kapoor-was-sanju-sir-271001.html|website=filmibeat.com|accessdate=25 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526115646/https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/news/2018/dia-mirza-on-dutt-biopic-people-who-went-on-the-sets-thought-ranbir-kapoor-was-sanju-sir-271001.html|archivedate=26 May 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Koirala also expressed that she was \"shocked at Ranbir's capacity to transform\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shetty |first1=Karishma |title=EXCLUSIVE \u2013 Manisha Koirala: Ranbir Kapoor is out for a bigger game than just being a SUPERSTAR |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/exclusives/exclusive-manisha-koirala-ranbir-kapoor-out-bigger-game-just-being-superstar-417570 |website=pinkvilla.com |publisher=PINKVILLA |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018}}</ref> Hirani also revealed that Kapoor was \"meeting Sanju separately...had a full timeline of how Sanju looked in the 80s, 90s, 2000s... and made a whole collection of look videos.\"<ref name=\"auto4\"/> Kapoor himself also stated that he \"knew that there is a fine line between mimicry and representing someone who is loved by so many people\" which is why \"it took us six to eight months to get ready... to prep, do the prosthetic tests, acting and character rehearsals.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Darade |first1=Pooja |title=Ranbir Kapoor: I understand that I'm one of the few privileged people who had it easy in life |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/ranbir-kapoor-i-understand-i-m-one-few-privileged-people-who-had-it-easy-life-416426 |website=pinkvilla.com |publisher=PINKVILLA |accessdate=19 June 2018 |date=19 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627115055/https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/ranbir-kapoor-i-understand-i-m-one-few-privileged-people-who-had-it-easy-life-416426 |archivedate=27 June 2018  }}</ref>\n\nKapoor further mentioned that whilst the physical transformation was significantly easier, emotional transformation and \"being able to understand the emotional level of the character was really daunting.\" However, he also revealed that as Dutt \"represents an epitome of body building and if I had to play him on screen, body was essential\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju behind the scenes: Ranbir Kapoor put hours in gym to look like Sanjay Dutt |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-behind-the-scenes-ranbir-kapoor-put-hours-in-gym-to-look-like-sanjay-dutt/articleshow/64884681.cms |website=mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com |publisher=Mumbai Mirror |accessdate=6 July 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref> In order to build his body like Dutt's, Kapoor revealed that it required \"sacrifice\" and \"discipline\" as he \"was having 8 meals a day, waking up at 3 in the morning to drink a protein shake.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chauhan |first1=Soumyata |title=Sanju: From having 8 meals a day to sitting 6 hours on makeup chair everyday, watch how Ranbir Kapoor became Sanjay Dutt |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-sanju-from-having-8-meals-a-day-to-sitting-6-hours-on-makeup-chair-everyday-watch-how-ranbir-kapoor-became-sanjay-dutt-2633860 |website=dnaindia.com |publisher=DNA India |accessdate=6 July 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref>  He also mentioned that he \"wanted to take a step back and didn\u2019t want to be around him too much because I didn\u2019t want to be obsessed with him. I would be always looking at him, trying to see what he is doing, how he is scratching his beard, how he is talking\u2026but before any poignant moment in the script, for instance, the jail sequence, the drug sequence, his mother\u2019s death, or when the TADA verdict (Terrorist and Disruptive Activities (Prevention) Act came, I would always call him the night before the shoot. I just wanted to know what he was feeling, and very graciously, very honestly he would tell me and I would express that on screen. I wanted to represent him with respect\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sinha |first1=Seema |title=Ranbir Kapoor on Sanju: Not a propaganda film but an honest portrayal of a flawed human being |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ranbir-kapoor-on-sanju-not-a-propaganda-film-but-an-honest-portrayal-of-a-flawed-human-being-4613381.html |website=firstpost.com |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629112604/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ranbir-kapoor-on-sanju-not-a-propaganda-film-but-an-honest-portrayal-of-a-flawed-human-being-4613381.html |archivedate=29 June 2018  }}</ref> and a \"true representation of what was going on in his head.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Syed |first1=Arub |title=Sanju: Ranbir Kapoor talks playing Sanjay Dutt |url=https://www.desiblitz.com/content/sanju-ranbir-kapoor-sanjay-dutt |website=desiblitz.com |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nHairstylist Aalim Hakim revealed that it took \"22 days to finalise Ranbir's different avatars\" as it was a \"challenge\" to create the \"receding hairline for Ranbir and give him a broad forehead\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bhalla |first1=Ankita |title='It took 22 days to turn Ranbir into Sanju!' \u2013 Celebrity hairstylist Aalim Hakim |url=https://www.peepingmoon.com/news/exclusive/it-took-22-days-to-turn-ranbir-kapoor-into-sanju-celebrity-hairstylist-aalim-hakim-79815/ |website=peepingmoon.com |accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref> Costumer designer Ekha Lakani, stated that in regards to Kapoor's costume, she \"discussed every look [with Kapoor]... spent hours trying to match every inch; how loose or how fitted it should be\" by \"matching different body types [as] Sanjay Dutt has had a different body type all throughout his life\".<ref name=\"auto6\">{{cite web |last1=Gupta |first1=Avantika |title=EXCLUSIVE: Ranbir Kapoor knew Sanjay Dutt in and out: Sanju's costume designer, Ekha Lakhani |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/fashion/celebrity-style/exclusive-ranbir-kapoor-knew-sanjay-dutt-and-out-sanju-s-costume-designer-eka-lakhani-417347 |website=pinkvilla.com |publisher=PINKVILLA |accessdate=25 June 2018 |date=25 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627115055/https://www.pinkvilla.com/fashion/celebrity-style/exclusive-ranbir-kapoor-knew-sanjay-dutt-and-out-sanju-s-costume-designer-eka-lakhani-417347 |archivedate=27 June 2018  }}</ref>\n\n[[Manisha Koirala]] who essays the character of [[Nargis]] in the film spoke about her transformation as well stating that \"we did a couple of tests, from when she had short hair to when she had long hair.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Shah|first1=Aashna|title=Sanjay Dutt Biopic: Presenting Manisha Koirala As Nargis|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/sanjay-dutt-biopic-presenting-manisha-koirala-as-nargis-1796363|website=ndtv.com|accessdate=25 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526080842/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/sanjay-dutt-biopic-presenting-manisha-koirala-as-nargis-1796363|archivedate=26 May 2018}}</ref> Koirala also revealed that she \"did a lot of research on Nargisji\" by studying \"various photographs, books [and] documentary\". She also admitted that it was \"traumatic\" reliving being a cancer patient as Koirala is an ovarian cancer survivor. She further mentioned that \"it required a lot of inner strength... but was finally worth it as she tried to \"capture [Nargis's] essence, the core of her being\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Correspondent |first1=HT |title=Manisha Koirala shares her many looks as Nargis in Sanju, says she has imbibed her soul |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/manisha-koirala-shares-her-many-looks-as-nargis-in-sanju-says-she-has-imbibed-her-soul/story-KFDfJpmQRgwM0J6MsRXreP.html |website=hindustantimes.com |publisher=Hindustan Times |accessdate=13 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612100611/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/manisha-koirala-shares-her-many-looks-as-nargis-in-sanju-says-she-has-imbibed-her-soul/story-KFDfJpmQRgwM0J6MsRXreP.html |archivedate=12 June 2018  }}</ref> Regarding Koirala's costume, Lakhani stated that Nargis' \"iconic images\" were taken and she then \"recreated a look on that from every curl or twist in the hair to the way the body was or the makeup\".<ref name=\"auto6\"/>\n\n[[Vicky Kaushal]] who's \"character's name is Kamlesh and is \"more like a brother\" to Dutt revealed that he \"went to Surat to study the body language and mannerism of Gujaratis\" as his character, although originally from India has been living in America for the maximum time so \"his Gujarati was ought to fade with time.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=D'Silva |first1=Russel |title=\"In real life, the person on whom my character is based, has been with Sanjay Dutt since his film film to date\": Vicky Kaushal |url=https://www.movified.com/in-real-life-the-person-on-whom-my-character-is-based-has-been-with-sanjay-dutt-since-his-film-film-to-date-vicky-kaushal |website=movified.com |accessdate=23 June 2018 |date=22 June 2018}}</ref> He also revealed that he went through a \"huge physical transformation\" by losing weight to \"look like a lean young Gujarati guy to an aged man of the present time\". He also stated that \"losing and gaining weight [brought a] change in the body language\" which thus enabled him get the \"right look\" and thus \"perform better\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=NS |first1=IA |title=Vicky Kaushal: I went though a huge physical transformation for Sanju |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vicky-kaushal-i-went-through-a-huge-physical-transformation-for-sanju-5221081/ |website=indianexpress.com |publisher=Indian Express |accessdate=17 June 2018 |date=17 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617094745/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vicky-kaushal-i-went-through-a-huge-physical-transformation-for-sanju-5221081/ |archivedate=17 June 2018  }}</ref>\n\n[[Paresh Rawal]] expressed that he prepared for his role by trying to \"maintain a distance off camera\" with Kapoor in order to \"stay true to the character\". He further added that \"we were not pals who would chat together in between the shots\" which went on to embody the real life relationship between Dutt and his father as [[Sunil Dutt]] \"loved his son to death but never had a friendly equation with [him]\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Paresh Rawal on playing Sunil Dutt in Sanju: Maintained distance from Ranbir Kapoor to stay true to character |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/paresh-rawal-on-playing-sunil-dutt-in-sanju-maintained-distance-from-ranbir-kapoor-to-stay-true-to-character-4541141.html |website=firstpost.com |publisher=First Post |accessdate=19 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620010650/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/paresh-rawal-on-playing-sunil-dutt-in-sanju-maintained-distance-from-ranbir-kapoor-to-stay-true-to-character-4541141.html |archivedate=20 June 2018  }}</ref> Rawal also stated that he could not \"look like Sunil Dutt\" following the look tests but had to \"portray the emotions, the 'jazba' (passion) that he had for the country, for his family and for his son\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Prabhas |first1=Madhuri |title=Ranbir Kapoor is not Recluse or Moody \u2013 Paresh Rawal opens up about his Reel Life Son from Sanju! |url=https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/news/2018/ranbir-kapoor-is-not-recluse-or-moody-paresh-rawal-opens-up-about-his-reel-life-son-from-sanju/articlecontent-pf255670-274844.html |website=filmibeat.com |publisher=FilmiBeat |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Dia Mirza]] however, stated that she prepared to play the role of Dutt's wife through \"workshops and look tests\" but also by studying some of the \"news clips released around the time\" as well as \"her interviews\" and \"body language\". Mirza also stated that she \"wanted to understand Maanayata as a wife, woman and mother handled the public scrutiny that she was subjected to\". She added that she mainly focussed on \"understanding and being honest to the emotion more than anything else.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nijhara |first1=Apoorva |title=Dia Mirza on Sanju :Sanjay Dutt and Maanayata's relationship is free of judgement |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/dia-mirza-sanju-sanjay-dutt-and-maanayata-s-relationship-free-judgement-417039 |website=pinkvilla.com |publisher=PINKVILLA |accessdate=23 June 2018 |language=English |date=23 June 2018}}</ref> Mirza also revealed that she had to \"dye [her] hair jet black\" and eventually saw herself as [[Manyata Dutt]] once she \"placed that mole on my face and saw myself in the mirror\" as she saw Maanayata in her \"reflection.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Parkar |first1=Shaheen |title=Dia Mirza: After placing mole on my face, I saw Maanayata |url=https://www.msn.com/en-in/entertainment/bollywood/dia-mirza-after-placing-mole-on-my-face-i-saw-maanayata/ar-AAyWGM2 |website=msn.com |accessdate=23 June 2018 |date=21 June 2018}}</ref> Mirza, also revealed that Maanayata was a \"rock\" in Dutt's life and with all \"sincerity and honesty [wanted to] understand \"what it meant to be a mother and a wife\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tulsiani |first1=Kriti |title=EXCLUSIVE: Sanju actor Dia Mirza reveals what she learnt about Sanjay Dutt and Maanyata Dutt's relationship |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/exclusive-sanju-actor-dia-mirza-reveals-what-she-learnt-about-sanjay-dutt-and-maanayata-dutts-relationship-while-doing-the-film/247204 |website=timesnownews.com |publisher=Times Now |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn [[Sonam Kapoor]]'s costume, Lakhani revealed that Kapoor's costume was designed to look like \"the girl next door, pretty, giving out very delicate vibes [with] really soft fabrics, pastel hues, delicate embroidery. Kapoor's costume was given \"peter pan collars in all her outfits... to make her from that era\" except that the team stayed away from making her look like a \"fashion diva\" but more \"real\".<ref name=\"auto6\"/>\n\nSpeaking about Sharma's character, Hirani mentioned in an interview that he wanted Sharma to look \"like an Indian who stayed in London and [was] brought up there\" which then led her to wearing a wig with voluptuous curly hair in the film.<ref>{{cite web |last1=V |first1=Aishwarya |title=EXCLUSIVE \u2013 Rajkumar Hirani on Anushka Sharma's look in Sanju: She asked 'Sir, you don't like my hair' |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/exclusives/exclusive-rajkumar-hirani-anushka-sharmas-look-sanju-she-asked-sir-you-dont-my-hair-416545 |website=pinkvilla.com |publisher=PINKVILLA |accessdate=19 June 2018 |date=19 June 2018}}</ref> Aditi Gautam, who plays Namrata Dutt revealed that she was cast as Hirani thought she looked \"exactly like\" Dutt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/sanju-actress-aditi-seiya-enjoys-bali-vacation-film-success/|title=Sanju actress Aditi Seiya enjoys Bali vacation after the film success :Latest Bollywood News - Bollywood Hungama|first=Bollywood|last=Hungama|date=12 July 2018}}</ref> Seiya further mentioned that she prepared for her role by watching interviews that allowed her to gauge on Dutt's \"strong personality...[which is also] poised and dignified.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roychoudhury |first1=Shibaji |title=Sanju: This actress hated playing Ranbir Kapoor's sister in the Rajkumar Hirani film, here's why |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/sanju-this-actress-hated-playing-ranbir-kapoor-s-sister-in-the-rajkumar-hirani-film-here-s-why/246240 |website=timesnownews.com |publisher=Times Now |accessdate=26 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627115055/https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/sanju-this-actress-hated-playing-ranbir-kapoor-s-sister-in-the-rajkumar-hirani-film-here-s-why/246240 |archivedate=27 June 2018  }}</ref>\n\n=== Principal photography ===\nShooting for the film began on 12 January 2017 with Ranbir Kapoor, Paresh Rawal, Dia Mirza and other cast and crew.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/happened-sanjay-dutt-paid-surprise-visit-sets-biopic-starring-ranbir-kapoor|title=What happened when Sanjay Dutt paid a surprise visit on the sets of his biopic starring Ranbir Kapoor&nbsp;\u2013 Bollywood Hungama|first=Bollywood|last=Hungama|date=27 January 2017|accessdate=25 March 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202234711/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/happened-sanjay-dutt-paid-surprise-visit-sets-biopic-starring-ranbir-kapoor/|archivedate=2 February 2017}}</ref> Shooting was wrapped on 21 January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sanjay-dutt-biopic-ranbir-kapoor-sonam-kapoor-rajkumar-hirani-dutts-the-way-watch-video-5034413/|title=Ranbir Kapoor, Sonam Kapoor wrap up Sanjay Dutt biopic with a fun video 'Dutts The Way' \u2013 Indian Express|date=22 January 2018|accessdate=22 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123072314/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sanjay-dutt-biopic-ranbir-kapoor-sonam-kapoor-rajkumar-hirani-dutts-the-way-watch-video-5034413/|archivedate=23 January 2018}}</ref> At the wrap party, the cast and crew were seen wearing personalised T-shirts with the hashtag \"#duttstheway\" in order to promote the film.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kulkarni|first1=Prachi|title=Dutt Biopic Wrap Up Inside Pics: Ranbir Kapoor, Sonam Kapoor and Crew Celebrating the Last day Leaves us Excited|url=https://www.latestly.com/entertainment/bollywood/dutt-biopic-wrap-up-inside-pics-ranbir-kapoor-sonam-kapoor-and-crew-celebrating-the-last-day-leaves-us-excited-6191.html|website=latestly.com|accessdate=25 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526113002/https://www.latestly.com/entertainment/bollywood/dutt-biopic-wrap-up-inside-pics-ranbir-kapoor-sonam-kapoor-and-crew-celebrating-the-last-day-leaves-us-excited-6191.html|archivedate=26 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nInitially, there were plans to bring Kapoor and Dutt together in the film at the end through a video chat where Dutt would interview Kapoor on his experience and journey. However, these plans were shelved due to both actor's prior commitments. Instead, the film will showcase both actors coming together in the form of a peppy dance number at the end credits.<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju: Sanjay Dutt's Cameo Still, Title Board & A Still With Anushka Sharma! |url=http://www.koimoi.com/bollywood-news/sanju-sanjay-dutts-cameo-still-title-board-a-still-with-anushka-sharma/ |website=koimoi.com |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628083650/http://www.koimoi.com/bollywood-news/sanju-sanjay-dutts-cameo-still-title-board-a-still-with-anushka-sharma/ |archivedate=28 June 2018  }}</ref> Hirani revealed that the original running time of the film as supposed to be 2 hours and 25 minutes. However, the running time was reduced with an entire song cut out of the film as it \"was obstructing the pace of the film and it was breaking the narrative\". Hirani further commented on this decision by stating that \"if you feel it does not work then you have to let it go.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Baskaran |first1=Swetha |title=\"THE FILM IS BIGGER THAN A PARTICULAR SCENE\" \u2013 RAJKUMAR HIRANI |url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/rajkumar-hiranis-latest-statement-about-sanju.html |website=behindwoods.com |accessdate=23 June 2018 |date=22 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180624010446/https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/rajkumar-hiranis-latest-statement-about-sanju.html |archivedate=24 June 2018  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju: Here's why Rajkumar Hirani removed a track from the final cut |url=http://www.freepressjournal.in/bollywood/sanju-heres-why-rajkumar-hirani-removed-a-track-from-the-final-cut/1301736 |website=freepressjournal.in |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=24 June 2018 |date=22 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nA replica of Dutt's childhood home which he lived in with his parents took 25 days to complete, as Hirani wanted to portray's Dutt's life right from childhood to present day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/mobile/news/features/rajkumar-hirani-recreates-sanjay-dutts-house-sanju-unbelievable/|title=Rajkumar Hirani RECREATES Sanjay Dutt's house for Sanju and it is UNBELIEVABLE!|website=www.bollywoodhungama.com|accessdate=29 June 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627230837/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/mobile/news/features/rajkumar-hirani-recreates-sanjay-dutts-house-sanju-unbelievable/|archivedate=27 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Sanju\n| type         = [[soundtrack]]\n| artist       = [[A. R. Rahman]], [[Rohan-Rohan]] and Vikram Montrose\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = {{start date|df=yes|2018|6|13}}\n| recorded     = 2017\u20132018\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 26:25\n| language     = [[Hindi]]\n| label        = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{External media\n| audio1 = {{YouTube|blXpa3yh2lw|Audio Jukebox}}}}\n{{Singles\n| name = Sanju\n| type = soundtrack\n| single1 = Main Badhiya Tu Bhi Badhiya\n| single1date = 23 May 2018\n| single2 = Kar Har Maidaan Fateh\n| single2date = 5 June 2018\n}}\n}}\n\nThe film's soundtrack features 6 songs composed by [[A. R. Rahman]], Rohan-Rohan and Vikram Montrose while lyrics are written by [[Irshad Kamil]], Shekhar Astitwa, Puneet Sharma, Rohan Gokhale and Abhijat Joshi. The [[film score]] is composed by Sanjay Wandrekar and Atul Raninga. [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]], the film's producer was initially dissatisfied with music and visuals for two songs. Instead of re-shooting the scenes with the songs, they decided to sign A. R. Rahman to compose original songs to fit in the same scenes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sanju-a-r-rahman-collaborates-with-rajkumar-hirani-for-the-films-soundtrack-4495115.html|title=Sanju: A R Rahman collaborates with Rajkumar Hirani for the film's soundtrack- Entertainment News, Firstpost|work=Firstpost|access-date=5 June 2018|language=en-US|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625141957/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sanju-a-r-rahman-collaborates-with-rajkumar-hirani-for-the-films-soundtrack-4495115.html|archivedate=25 June 2018}}</ref> Rahman was roped in as a guest composer and has composed two songs for the movie including ''\"[[Ruby Ruby]]\"'', with lyrics penned by his regular collaborator Irshad Kamil. The first single, \"Main Badhiya Tu Bhi Badhiya\", was released on 23 May 2018 voiced by [[Sonu Nigam]] and [[Sunidhi Chauhan]]. The second single, \"Kar Har Maidaan Fateh\" was released on 5 June 2018 sung by [[Shreya Ghoshal]] and [[Sukhwinder Singh]].\n\nThe album of the film was released by [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]] on 13 June 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/sanju-original-motion-picture-soundtrack-ep/1405546157|title=Sanju (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)|publisher=[[iTunes]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706104838/https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/sanju-original-motion-picture-soundtrack-ep/1405546157|archivedate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| headline = Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title14 = \n| length14 = \n| title15 = \n| length15 = \n| title16 = \n| length16 = \n| title17 = \n| length17 = \n| title18 = \n| length18 = \n| title19 = \n| length19 = \n| title20 = \n| length20 = \n| total_length = {{Duration|m=26|s=25}}\n| title1 = Main Badhiya Tu Bhi Badhiya\n| extra1 = [[Sonu Nigam]], [[Sunidhi Chauhan]]\n| lyrics1 = Puneet Sharma\n| music1 = Rohan-Rohan\n| length1 = 4:34\n| title2 = Kar Har Maidaan Fateh\n| extra2 = [[Shreya Ghoshal]], [[Sukhwinder Singh]]\n| lyrics2 = Shekhar Astitwa\n| music2 = Vikram Montrose\n| length2 = 5:11\n| title3 = [[Ruby Ruby]]\n| extra3 = Shashwat Singh, [[Poorvi Koutish]]\n| lyrics3 = [[Irshad Kamil]]\n| music3 = [[A. R. Rahman]]\n| length3 = 4:45\n| title4 = Baba Bolta Hain Bas Ho Gaya\n| extra4 = [[Papon (Assamese singer)|Papon]], Ranbir Kapoor, Supriya Pathak\n| lyrics4 = Puneet Sharma, Abhijat Joshi, Rohan Gokhale\n| music4 = Vikram Montrose\n| length4 = 4:45\n| title5 = Bhopu Baj Raha Hain\n| extra5 = [[Nakash Aziz]]\n| lyrics5 = Shekhar Astitwa, Rohan Gokhale\n| music5 = Rohan-Rohan\n| length5 = 4:03\n| title6 = Mujhe Chaand Pe Le Chalo\n| extra6 = [[Nikhita Gandhi]]\n| title7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| title11 = \n| length11 = \n| title12 = \n| length12 = \n| title13 = \n| length13 = \n| lyrics6 = Irshad Kamil\n| music6 = A. R. Rahman\n| length6 = 3:07\n}}\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nA short official teaser of the film was released on 24 April 2018.<ref name=hindu>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/teaser-of-sanjay-dutt-biopic-sanju-out/article23657078.ece|title=Teaser of Sanjay Dutt biopic Sanju out|accessdate=25 April 2018|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> It became the highest viewed Hindi film teaser of all time, garnering more than 30 million views within the first 48 hours of its release and 150 million global views across several social media platforms.<ref name=midday>{{cite web|title=Sanju teaser clocks 150 million views worldwide|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/sanju-teaser-clocks-150-million-views-worldwide/19363164|website=mid-day.com|publisher=mid-day.com|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508054001/https://www.mid-day.com/articles/sanju-teaser-clocks-150-million-views-worldwide/19363164|archivedate=8 May 2018}}</ref> The marketing campaign of the film started with the teaser launch which appeared on \"a roadblock on 80 channels across the Star network for the teaser launch, cashing in on the Indian Premier League traffic on TV as well as its streaming app Hotstar\".<ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite web |last1=Jha |first1=Lata |title=Sanju makers go digital for Ranbir Kapoor's acid test |url=http://origin-alpha.livemint.com/Consumer/hrFHJz8l3moXlb9CYL5TwO/Sanju-makers-go-digital-for-Ranbir-Kapoors-acid-test.html |website=livemint.com |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018}}</ref> The official trailer was released on 30 May 2018 and accumulated over 20 million views within its first 24 hours of release.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Correspondent |first1=HT |title=Sanju trailer: Watch it for Sanjay Dutt's unbelievable life, Ranbir Kapoor's performance |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sanju-trailer-watch-it-for-sanjay-dutt-s-unbelievable-life-ranbir-kapoor-s-performance/story-vWpLrpgCtypz2TstI1sRhI.html |website=hindustantimes.com |accessdate=30 May 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530233339/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sanju-trailer-watch-it-for-sanjay-dutt-s-unbelievable-life-ranbir-kapoor-s-performance/story-vWpLrpgCtypz2TstI1sRhI.html |archivedate=30 May 2018  }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/sanju-trailer-ranbir-kapoor-as-sanjay-dutt-is-brilliant-you-will-laugh-and-cry-with-him-1859891|title=Sanju Trailer: Ranbir Kapoor As Sanjay Dutt Is Brilliant. You Will Laugh And Cry With Him|work=NDTV.com|access-date=2 June 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180601114419/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/sanju-trailer-ranbir-kapoor-as-sanjay-dutt-is-brilliant-you-will-laugh-and-cry-with-him-1859891|archivedate=1 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Dia promotes sanju.jpg|thumb|right| Mirza promoting the film]]\n\nThe first poster was released on 30 April 2018 in which Kapoor looked as Sanjay Dutt when he first came out of jail in 2016. The next day, another poster was released showcasing another still of Kapoor as Dutt in 2016 leaving Yerwada jail.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sanju new poster: Ranbir Kapoor nails Sanjay Dutt's look from 2016 when he walked out of Yerwada jail|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-new-poster-ranbir-kapoor-nails-sanjay-dutts-look-from-2016-when-he-walked-out-of-yerwada-jail/articleshow/63969906.cms|website=MumbaiMirror.com|publisher=Mirror Online|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508122940/https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-new-poster-ranbir-kapoor-nails-sanjay-dutts-look-from-2016-when-he-walked-out-of-yerwada-jail/articleshow/63969906.cms|archivedate=8 May 2018}}</ref> Subsequently, more posters were released portraying Kapoor as Dutt from the 90s and 2003 when the films ''[[Rocky (1981 film)|Rocky]]'' and ''[[Munna Bhai M.B.B.S]]'' were released respectively.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sanju new poster: Ranbir Kapoor looks like a spitting image of Sanjay Dutt from the 90s|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/sanju-new-poster-ranbir-kapoor-sanjay-dutt-90s-look-1224780-2018-05-02|website=IndiaToday.in|publisher=IndiaToday.in|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180502234137/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/sanju-new-poster-ranbir-kapoor-sanjay-dutt-90s-look-1224780-2018-05-02|archivedate=2 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ranbir Kapoor as Munna Bhai in Sanju|url=http://www.businesssandesh.in/ranbir-kapoor-as-munna-bhai-in-sanju/|website=BusinessSandhesh.in|publisher=BusinessSandhesh.in|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508054948/http://www.businesssandesh.in/ranbir-kapoor-as-munna-bhai-in-sanju/|archivedate=8 May 2018}}</ref> On 7 May, Hirani released another poster.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Team|first1=koimoi.com|title=Sanju New Poster: After Munnabhai, Ranbir Kapoor Masters This Look Of Sanjay Dutt!|url=http://www.koimoi.com/bollywood-news/sanju-new-poster-after-munnabhai-ranbir-kapoor-masters-this-look-of-sanjay-dutt/|website=koimoi.com|publisher=koimoi.com|accessdate=7 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180507150538/http://www.koimoi.com/bollywood-news/sanju-new-poster-after-munnabhai-ranbir-kapoor-masters-this-look-of-sanjay-dutt/|archivedate=7 May 2018}}</ref> Hirani then announced that he would now release poster stills of the rest of the cast and crew until the trailer release date.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hirani|first1=Rajkumar|title=Time for #Sanju trailer to be unveiled. 30th May it is. Before that will introduce you to rest of the cast. Will post new posters everyday from tomorrow. #RanbirKapoor #RajkumarHiraniFilms @VVCFilms @foxstarhindi|url=https://twitter.com/RajkumarHirani/status/999591851719053313|website=twitter.com|accessdate=28 May 2018}}</ref>\nOn 25 May, Hirani released a still of \"Sanju's crazy romantic love life\" on Twitter presenting Kapoor and [[Sonam Kapoor]].<ref name=\"auto5\"/>  The next day a still of Kapoor was released presenting [[Paresh Rawal]] who play's Dutt's father. Following this, a still of actor [[Vicky Kaushal]] was released confirming his role as Dutt's best friend in USA.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Narayan|first1=Shreya|title=Who is Kumar Gaurav? Vicky Kaushal's look as Sanjay Dutt's best friend in Sanju revealed [Photo]|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/who-kumar-gaurav-vicky-kaushals-look-sanjay-dutts-best-friend-sanju-revealed-photo-770356|website=ibtimes.co.in|publisher=International Business Times|accessdate=28 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180528144938/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/who-kumar-gaurav-vicky-kaushals-look-sanjay-dutts-best-friend-sanju-revealed-photo-770356|archivedate=28 May 2018}}</ref> Hirani released a still of [[Anushka Sharma]] the day after but did not reveal her role, as he intended for the trailer to do so instead. At the trailer launch Hirani told that the character of [[Anushka Sharma]] is actually a comprised role of him and the writer, [[Abhijat Joshi]] showing that how they both collected the whole story about [[Sanjay Dutt]] .<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nijhara|first1=Apoorva|title=Sanju: Rajkumar Hirani reveals Anushka Sharma's look; BUT keeps her character a mystery|url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/sanju-rajkumar-hirani-reveals-anushka-sharmas-look-keeps-her-character-mystery-413885|website=pinkvilla.com|publisher=PINKVILLA|accessdate=29 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627115055/https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/sanju-rajkumar-hirani-reveals-anushka-sharmas-look-keeps-her-character-mystery-413885|archivedate=27 June 2018}}</ref> A still of Manisha Koirala playing Nargis was also released by Hirani.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shekhar |first1=Mimansa |title=Sanju poster: Manisha Koirala bears a striking resemblance to Nargis |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-poster-manisha-koirala-nargis-photo-5206121/ |website=indianexpress.com |publisher=Indian Express |accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref> \nAfter that, Rajkumar Hirani had released the last poster in which, [[Dia Mirza]] was seen as [[Manyata Dutt]].\n\nHirani released postcard stills of two prominent elements of the film and Dutt's life: the first showed a still of Kapoor begging on the streets in order to buy a bus ticket to meet a friend, whilst the second presented him at the premiere of his debut film ''[[Rocky (1981 film)|Rocky]]'', just three days after losing his mother to cancer.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bureau |first1=NH |title='Sanju' New poster reveals shocking facts about Sanjay Dutt's life |url=https://www.newsheads.in/entertainment/bollywood-news/sanju-new-poster-reveals-shocking-facts-about-sanjay-dutt-life/article/15778.html |website=newsheads.in |publisher=newsheads |accessdate=17 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618002949/https://www.newsheads.in/entertainment/bollywood-news/sanju-new-poster-reveals-shocking-facts-about-sanjay-dutt-life/article/15778.html |archivedate=18 June 2018  }}</ref> Aside from poster releases, marketing was also successful through \"Sanju-style lip sync and face filters and post videos to win prizes\" across social media.<ref name=\"auto7\"/> Actress [[Karishma Tanna]] also released a still of herself with Kapoor and Kaushal on 20 June, confirming that she would be appearing in the film in a \"fun song\" with the two actors.<ref name=\"20 June 2018\">{{cite web |title=Sanju: Ranbir Kapoor, Vicky Kaushal, Karishma Tanna on new still |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-ranbir-kapoor-vicky-kaushal-karishma-tanna-new-still-1502651142.html |website=thestatesman.com |accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju: Karishma Tanna's first look as Madhuri Dixit out from Ranbir Kapoor starrer film |url=http://www.catchnews.com/bollywood-news/sanju-karishma-tanna-s-first-look-as-madhuri-dixit-came-out-from-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-film-118698.html |website=catchnews.com |accessdate=24 June 2018 |date=20 June 2018}}</ref> On 19 July, the song was released as ''Bhophu Baj Raha Hai\n'' ''which didn't make it to the final cut, though was released promotionally on'' [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Prabhas |first1=Madhuri |title=Bhopu Baj Raha Hai: This Deleted Song From Sanju Will Make You Hit The Dance Floor Right Away! |url=https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/news/2018/bhopu-baj-raha-hai-this-deleted-song-from-sanju-will-make-you-hit-the-dance-floor-right-away-275504.html |website=filmibeat.com |accessdate=19 July 2018 |date=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn Father's Day, the makers released second teaser of the film, starring a clip of Kapoor and Rawal essaying the father-son bond between Dutt and his father. The clip was promoted along with the hashtag \"#JaaduKiJhappi\" (the magic of a hug), a line made famous by Sanjay in ''[[Munna Bhai M.B.B.S.]]''<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sharma |first1=Pooja |title='Sanju' new poster: Paresh Rawal gives a 'Jaadu ki Jhappi' to Ranbir Kapoor |url=https://www.bollywoodbubble.com/bollywood-news/sanju-new-poster-paresh-rawal-gives-a-jaadu-ki-jhappi-to-ranbir-kapoor/ |website=bollywoodbubble.com |publisher=Bollywood Bubble |accessdate=17 June 2018 |date=17 June 2018}}</ref> A third teaser of the film was released on 22 June presenting Kapoor playing Dutt as Munna Bhai.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Des |first1=Chayanika |title=Ranbir Kapoor Recreates The Classroom Scene from Munna Bhai M.B.B.S in New Sanju Teaser \u2013 Watch Teaser |url=http://www.india.com/showbiz/bollywood-news-new-sanju-teaser-out-ranbir-kapoor-recreate-classroom-scene-from-munnai-bhai-m-b-b-s-watch-teaser-3125015/ |website=india.com |accessdate=23 June 2018 |date=22 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180624012158/http://www.india.com/showbiz/bollywood-news-new-sanju-teaser-out-ranbir-kapoor-recreate-classroom-scene-from-munnai-bhai-m-b-b-s-watch-teaser-3125015/ |archivedate=24 June 2018  }}</ref> Kapoor also promoted the film by making a rare appearance on social media as he took over the Twitter handle of Fox Star studios and was involved in a live tweet session with fans and shared personal childhood pictures of himself during Father's Day.<ref name=\"auto7\"/>\n\nShikha Kapur, CEO of [[Fox Star Studios]] stated that the marketing \"objective was to build conversations and scale\" without [defining the film's] target group by age and geography but by affinities and behaviours online. She further mentioned that the \"crux of the marketing narrative\" was that the film is \"of a man who lived many lives in one life and a story that is so unbelievable that you almost want to pinch yourself and ask if it really happened\". [[Saurabh Uboweja]], international brand expert and CEO of [[Brands of Desire]], stated that [the marketing campaign is about] \"the ability to engage, crack some jokes and have fun backed by very strong messaging\" which is why \"less than 10%\" of budgeting has been spent on marketing compared to a usual big-ticket Bollywood film that would spend 20\u201325% on. He also mentioned that \"making Dutt appear flawed, yet sensitive and relatable is also a means to reach out to a generation for which the actor is past his prime\" and to \"drive entire families\" out to watch the film.<ref name=\"auto7\"/>\n\nActivist Prithvi Mhaske raised objection over the toilet leakage scene shown in the trailer of the film through a letter sent to the Central Board of Film Certification (CBFC). The letter stated that \"the government and authorities are taking a very well care of all the barracks of the jails\" indicating that \"this particular scene will make a bad impression about the jails and jail authorities of the Indians\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nijhara |first1=Apoorva |title=An activist Prithvi Mhaske has raised an objection on the toilet leakage scene in the barrack of jail picturised in the movie, Sanju. |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/sanju-activist-raises-objection-jails-toilet-leakage-scene-ranbir-kapoors-film-415708 |website=pinkvilla.com |publisher=PINKVILLA |accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Gaikwal |first1=Pramod |title=Sanju trailer: Toilet leakage scene in jail from Ranbir Kapoor-starrer may land in legal trouble |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sanju-trailer-toilet-leakage-scene-jail-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-may-land-legal-trouble-771862 |website=ibtimes.co.in |publisher=International Business Times |accessdate=13 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615155514/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sanju-trailer-toilet-leakage-scene-jail-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-may-land-legal-trouble-771862 |archivedate=15 June 2018  }}</ref> On 25 June, it was reported that the censor board had cleared the film and finalised it for release in India. There has been one scene involving the overflowing toilet from Dutt's jail cell to be removed and a few dialogues.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jha |first1=Subhash K |title=Censor board clears Sanju |url=http://www.asianage.com/entertainment/bollywood/260618/censor-board-clears-sanju.html |website=asianage.com |accessdate=25 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627115056/http://www.asianage.com/entertainment/bollywood/260618/censor-board-clears-sanju.html |archivedate=27 June 2018  }}</ref> Social activist Gaurav Gulati also filed to the National Commission for Women believing the film \"contains derogatory words for women\" to which sex worker's \"identity [is] being demeaned\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tiwari |first1=Khushboo |title=EXCLUSIVE: Social activist talks about his complaint against 'Sanju' team |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/exclusive-social-activist-talks-about-his-complaint-against-sanju-team/articleshow/64767948.cms |website=timesofindia.com |publisher=Times of India |accessdate=28 June 2018 |date=28 June 2018}}</ref> Despite being cleared by the censor board in India, the film was granted a 15 certificate in [[Great Britain]] due to \u201cdrug references, drug misuse, infrequent strong sex references.\"<ref>{{cite web |title='Sanju' overseas box-office collection: The Rajkumar directorial starring Ranbir Kapoor scores big in overseas |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/64814170.cms |website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=5 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Box office ==\n=== India ===\n''Sanju'' has a final worldwide gross of {{INRConvert|586.85|c}}.<ref name=\"BH-Sanju\">{{cite web |title=Sanju Box Office Collection till Now |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/sanju/box-office/ |website=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref> Advance bookings for the film began on 24 June.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sanju: Advance booking for the Ranbir Kapoor starrer begins |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-advance-booking-ranbir-kapoor-film-5231536/|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=30 June 2018 |date=25 June 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625072304/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-advance-booking-ranbir-kapoor-film-5231536/|archivedate=25 June 2018  }}</ref> It was released across 4200 screens in India,<ref name=\"2.0five\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=4491|title=2.0 All India Day Five Update - Maintains Very Well - Box Office India|website=www.boxofficeindia.com}}</ref> and over 1300 screens overseas.<ref name=\"overseas1\">{{cite web|title=Box Office: Sanju Day 1 in overseas|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-sanju-day-1-overseas/|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|date=29 June 2018|accessdate=30 June 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629202149/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-sanju-day-1-overseas/|archivedate=29 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe film opened to an occupancy of 85% in the domestic theatres.<ref>{{cite web|title=BO update: Sanju takes a flying start with 85% occupancy rate|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-update/bo-update-sanju-takes-flying-start-85-occupancy-rate/|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|date=29 June 2018|accessdate=30 June 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629104301/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-update/bo-update-sanju-takes-flying-start-85-occupancy-rate/|archivedate=29 June 2018}}</ref> It collected {{INRConvert|34.75|c}} nett on its opening day at the domestic box office, which was the highest for all [[2018 in film|films released in India in 2018]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Box Office: Sanju takes the best opening of 2018, collects Rs. 34.75 crore|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-sanju-takes-best-opening-2018-collects-rs-34-75-crore/|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|date=30 June 2018|last=Tuteja|first=Joginder|accessdate=30 June 2018}}</ref> The film became Hirani's highest opening ever surpassing {{INRConvert|26.63|c}} collected by ''[[PK (film)|PK]]'' in 2014.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chauhan |first1=Gaurang |title=Sanju box office collection: Here are all the records broken by Ranbir Kapoor starrer |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/sanju-box-office-collection-here-are-all-the-records-broken-by-ranbir-kapoor-starrer/249521 |website=timesnownews.com |accessdate=5 July 2018 |date=4 July 2018}}</ref> It recorded the highest second day collection ever for a Hindi film domestically.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-sanju-records-highest-day-2-saturday-bollywood/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=1 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701155836/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-sanju-records-highest-day-2-saturday-bollywood/ |archivedate=1 July 2018  }}</ref> It collected over {{INRConvert|46.71|c}} nett on its third day, setting the record for the highest single day collecting ever for a Hindi film in India, surpassing ''[[Baahubali 2: The Conclusion]]''{{'}}s dubbed Hindi nett, while also becoming the highest weekend earner of the year.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/ranbir-kapoor-s-sanju-lords-over-box-office-earns-rs-72-50-cr-in-two-days/story-qoaig3a89OGVq55EBLM2XN.html|title=Sanju box office collection: Ranbir Kapoor film destroys Baahubali's record, earns Rs 120 cr in 3 days|date=1 July 2018|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|access-date=2 July 2018|language=en|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702121945/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/ranbir-kapoor-s-sanju-lords-over-box-office-earns-rs-72-50-cr-in-two-days/story-qoaig3a89OGVq55EBLM2XN.html|archivedate=2 July 2018}}</ref> The film entered the [[100 crore club]] in nett domestically within its first three days of release.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sarkar |first1=Suparno |title=Sanju day 7 box office collection: Rajkumar Hirani scores first Rs 200-crore film for Ranbir Kapoor |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sanju-day-7-box-office-collection-rajkumar-hirani-scores-first-rs-200-crore-film-ranbir-kapoor-774054 |website=ibtimes.co.in |accessdate=5 July 2018 |date=5 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706104838/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sanju-day-7-box-office-collection-rajkumar-hirani-scores-first-rs-200-crore-film-ranbir-kapoor-774054 |archivedate=6 July 2018  }}</ref> Despite it being a non-holiday and with reduced tickets, the film collected {{INRConvert|25.35|c}} nett on its first Monday.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju box office collection day 4: Ranbir Kapoor, Anushka Sharma-starrer set to hit the Rs 200 crore-mark |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-box-office-collection-day-4-ranbir-kapoor-anushka-sharma-starrer-set-to-hit-the-rs-200-crore-mark/articleshow/64839118.cms |website=mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com |accessdate=3 July 2018 |date=3 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703150714/https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sanju-box-office-collection-day-4-ranbir-kapoor-anushka-sharma-starrer-set-to-hit-the-rs-200-crore-mark/articleshow/64839118.cms |archivedate=3 July 2018  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju box office day 4: Ranbir Kapoor's film defeats Monday woes, earns a record Rs 145.41 crore |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sanju-box-office-day-4-ranbir-kapoor-s-film-defeats-monday-woes-earns-a-record-rs-145-41-crore/story-nXoJc2X9nbiV46SBxQB9AM.html |website=hindustantimes.com |publisher=Hindustan Times |accessdate=3 July 2018 |date=3 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703083230/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sanju-box-office-day-4-ranbir-kapoor-s-film-defeats-monday-woes-earns-a-record-rs-145-41-crore/story-nXoJc2X9nbiV46SBxQB9AM.html |archivedate=3 July 2018  }}</ref> Within its first week of release, ''Sanju'' had entered the 200 crore club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju box office collection day 7: Ranbir Kapoor film earns Rs 202.51 crore |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/box-office-collection/sanju-movie-box-office-collection-day-7-200-crore-mark-5247527/ |website=indianexpress.com |publisher=Indian Express |accessdate=6 July 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref> It also became the highest first week grosser of 2018,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mulasi |first1=Pankhurie |title=Sanju Crosses 200 Crore Mark, Becomes Highest First Week Grosser Of 2018 |url=http://www.movietalkies.com/news/sanju-crosses-200-crore-mark-becomes-highest-first-week-grosser-2018/ |website=movietalkies.com |accessdate=6 July 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref> the fourth highest week of all time and also became the first Hindi film to have a non-holiday release and yet still earn over 200 crores in its first week of running.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Farooqi |first1=Maryam |title=Sanju earns Rs 200 crore in opening week, records 4th highest first week of all time |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/sanju-earns-rs-200-crore-in-opening-week-records-4th-highest-first-week-of-all-time-2680711.html |website=moneycontrol.com |accessdate=6 July 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref> Therefore, ''Sanju'' also became Kapoor's first film to earn over 200 crores.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Handoo |first1=Ritika |title=Sanju Box Office collections: Ranbir Kapoor gets his first Rs 200 cr film! |url=http://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/sanju-box-office-collections-ranbir-kapoor-gets-his-first-rs-200-cr-film-2122612.html |website=zeenews.india.com |accessdate=6 July 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn its second weekend, the film earned {{INRConvert|12.50|c}} on Friday,<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju Box-Office collection: Sanju keeps up a decent job on second Friday, earns Rs. 12.50 crore |url=http://www.zeebiz.com/india/news-sanju-box-office-collection-sanju-keeps-up-a-decent-job-on-second-friday-earns-rs-1250-crore-54248 |website=zeebiz.com |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> {{INRConvert|21.50|c}} on Saturday and {{INRConvert|28|c}} on Sunday.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju 9th Day Box Office Collection, Surpasses Avengers Infinity War by 2nd Saturday |url=http://boxofficecollection.in/box-office-report/sanju-9th-day-box-office-collection-surpasses-avengers-infinity-war-by-2nd-saturday-36325 |website=boxofficecollection.in |accessdate=8 July 2018 |date=8 July 2018}}</ref> The film thus entered the 250 crore club within 10 days of release.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Farooqi |first1=Maryam |title=Sanju enters Rs 300-crore club, becomes seventh Bollywood film to achieve the feat |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/sanju-enters-rs-300-crore-club-is-the-seventh-bollywood-film-to-achieve-the-feat-2716771.html |website=moneycontrol.com |accessdate=16 July 2018 |date=16 July 2018}}</ref> The film also recorded the fourth highest second grossing week of all time, with approximately {{INRConvert|90|c}}.<ref>{{cite web |title='Sanju' box-office collection Day 14: Ranbir Kapoor starrer |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/box-office/sanju-box-office-collection-day-14-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-records-fourth-highest-second-week-collections-of-all-time/articleshow/64973286.cms |website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=13 July 2018}}</ref> At of the end of its second week run, ''Sanju'' had grossed {{INRConvert|500.43|c}} globally.<ref name=\"auto8\">{{cite web |last1=Roychoudhury |first1=Shibaji |title=Sanju box office collection: The Ranbir Kapoor starrer makes over Rs 500 crore worldwide |url=http://www.india.com/showbiz/bollywood-news-sanju-box-office-collection-ranbir-kapoors-film-is-unstoppable-enters-the-500-crore-club-globally-3165242/ |website=timesnownews.com |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=13 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn its third weekend, the film entered the 300 crore club and became Kapoor's first film<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju box office collection day 17: The Ranbir Kapoor starrer earns Rs 316.64 crore|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/box-office-collection/sanju-movie-box-office-collection-day-17-5260603/ |website=indianexpress.com |accessdate=16 July 2018 |date=16 July 2018}}</ref> and the 7th film of all time to reach this milestone.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ranbir Kapoor's Sanju becomes 7th film to gross Rs 300 crore |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/entertainment/bollywood/ranbir-kapoors-sanju-becomes-7th-film-gross-rs-300-crore-1502661836.html |website=thestatesman.com |accessdate=16 July 2018 |date=16 July 2018}}</ref> The film also surpassed the domestic lifetime collections of the {{INRConvert|302.15|c}} earned by ''[[Padmaavat]]'' to become the [[List of highest domestic net collection of Hindi films|highest grossing domestic nett collector of 2018]] and the 9th [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films of all time]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chauhan |first1=Gaurang |title=Sanju box office collection day 17: Ranbir Kapoor starrer beats Padmaavat; becomes the 5th highest grosser |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/sanju-box-office-collection-day-17-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-beats-padmaavat-becomes-the-5th-highest-grossing-bollywood-film-of-all-time/255097 |website=timesnownews.com |accessdate=16 July 2018 |date=16 July 2018}}</ref> The film thus registered the highest third week collections of 2018 as well.<ref>{{cite web |title=Box Office: Sanju registers the highest third weekend collections of 2018 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-sanju-registers-highest-third-weekend-collections-2018/ |website=bollywoodhungama.com |accessdate=17 July 2018 |date=17 July 2018}}</ref> By its third Tuesday, ''Sanju'''s domestic total reached {{INRConvert|321.57|c}}. The film therefore surpassed the lifetime domestic collections of {{INRConvert|320.34|c}} collected by ''[[Bajrangi Bhaijaan]]'' to become the fifth highest grossing Hindi film of all time.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roychoudhury |first1=Shibaji |title=Sanju box office collection day 19: Ranbir Kapoor starrer beats Bajrangi Bhaijaan; becomes 4th highest grosser |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/sanju-box-office-collection-day-19-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-beats-salman-khans-bajrangi-bhaijaan-becomes-4th-highest-grosser-of-all-time/256150 |website=timesnownews.com |accessdate=18 July 2018 |date=18 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe film's fourth week total was approximately {{INRConvert|10.48|c}} and {{INRConvert|337.28|c}} overall.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ranbir Kapoor's Sanju may surpass Salman Khan's Tiger Zinda Hai and Aamir Khan's PK at the Box Office |url=http://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/ranbir-kapoors-sanju-may-surpass-salman-khans-tiger-zinda-hai-and-aamir-khans-pk-at-the-box-office-2128150.html |website=zeenews.india.com |accessdate=27 July 2018 |date=27 July 2018}}</ref> Sanju thus surpassed the lifetime domestic nett collections of ''[[Tiger Zinda Hai]]''<ref>{{cite web |title=Ranbir Kapoor's Sanju becomes 4th highest grossing Indian film EVER; beats Salman-Katrina's Tiger Zinda Hai |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/ranbir-kapoor-s-sanju-becomes-4th-highest-grossing-indian-film-ever-beats-salman-katrinas-tiger-zinda-hai |website=pinkvilla.com |accessdate=30 July 2018}}</ref> and ''[[PK (film)|PK]]'' to become the second [[List of highest domestic net collection of Hindi films|highest-grossing film (nett)]] of all time.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Khurrana |first1=Amman |title=Sanju box office collection Day 33: Ranbir Kapoor-starrer beats PK to become all-time second-highest grosser |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/sanju-box-office-collection-day-33-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-beats-pk-to-become-all-time-second-highest-grosser/262993 |website=timesnownews.com |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Choudhury |first1=Sagarika |title=Ranbir Kapoor is the new box office KING as Sanju defeats Salman Khan's Bajrangi Bhaijaan and Aamir Khan's PK |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/ranbir-kapoor-new-box-office-king-sanju-defeats-salman-khans-bajrangi-bhaijaan-and-aamir-khans-pk-422340 |website=pinkvilla.com |accessdate=4 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Overseas ===\nThe film opened overseas with an estimated collection of {{INRConvert|1.32|c}} in [[Australia]], {{INRConvert|33.00|l}} in [[New Zealand]], {{INRConvert|1.19|c}} in [[United Kingdom]], and {{INRConvert|1.11|c}} in the [[United States]].<ref name=\"overseas1\"/> ''Sanju'' debuted at number 8 at the US box office in the opening weekend, earning more than ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' and ''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]'' in the same week on a comparatively lower number of 356 screens.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/sanju-box-office-collection-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-beats-avengers-infinity-war-solo-a-star-wars-story-in-the-us/249089|title=Sanju box office collection: Ranbir Kapoor starrer beats Avengers: Infinity War & Solo in the US|publisher=}}</ref> Its opening week collection was {{USD}}2.5 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/01/movies/sicario-day-of-the-soldado-box-office-jurassic-world.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=4 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701212757/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/01/movies/sicario-day-of-the-soldado-box-office-jurassic-world.html |archivedate=1 July 2018  }}</ref> The film also opened to an earning of {{PKR|3.2 crore}} in [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanju performs exceedingly well in Pakistan |url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/337447-|work=[[The News International]]|accessdate=4 July 2018 |date=4 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704055148/https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/337447-sanju-performs-exceedingly-well-in-pakistan |archivedate=4 July 2018 }}</ref> In [[Dubai]], the government allowed cinemas to remain open for 24 hours on Friday and Saturday to prevent crowd frenzy, causing shows to start as early as 4:30 am.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/sanju-fever-theatres-in-dubai-will-remain-open-for-24-hours-due-to-high-demand-for-the-film/articleshow/64850393.cms|title='Sanju' fever: Theatres in Dubai will remain open for 24 hours due to high demand for the film|date=4 July 2018|publisher=|via=The Economic Times}}</ref> In the [[Gulf Cooperation Council|GCC]], the film opened to earnings of {{INRConvert|6.19|c}}, along with a collection of {{INRConvert|34.90|c}} in [[Norway]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Farooqi |first1=Maryam |title=Sanju gets a warm welcome globally, opens in over 1,300 screens and scores Rs 55 cr |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/sanju-gets-a-warm-welcome-globally-opens-in-over-1300-screens-and-scores-rs-55-cr-2675671.html |website=moneycontrol.com |accessdate=5 July 2018 |date=5 July 2018}}</ref> Overseas, the film has garnered {{INRConvert|122|c}} as of two weeks of its initial release.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/sanju-box-office-report-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-crosses-rs-500-cr-mark-at-worldwide-collections-2124424.html |title= Sanju Box Office report: Ranbir Kapoor starrer crosses Rs 500 cr mark at worldwide collections |website=zeenews.india.com |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=13 July 2018}}</ref> CEO of [[Fox Star Studios]], Vijay Singh went on to confirm that ''Sanju'' was the biggest Indian \"film ever for Pakistan<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/sanju-4th-weekend-business-pakistan-beat-punjab-nahi-jaungi|title=SANJU BECOMES ALL TIME HIGHEST GROSSER IN PAKISTAN :: BEATS PUNJAB NAHI JAUNGI|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=23 July 2018|website=boxofficedetail.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-2-3rd-weekend-business-pakistan-becomes-all-time-highest-grosser/ |title= JAWANI PHIR NAHI ANI 2 3RD WEEKEND BUSINESS PAKISTAN :: BECOMES ALL TIME HIGHEST GROSSER|date=10 September 2018|accessdate=10 September 2018|website=boxofficedetail.com}}</ref> and Australia and the second biggest for US.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Srivastava |first1=Swikriti |title=Sanju Box Office: Ranbir Kapoor To Break The Highest Record Of Salman Khan; Rivalry To Get Intense |url=https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/box-office/2018/sanju-box-office-ranbir-kapoor-to-break-highest-record-salman-khan-rivalry-to-get-intense/articlecontent-pf258168-275476.html |website=filmibeat.com |accessdate=19 July 2018 |date=18 July 2018}}</ref> Due to popular demand, Singh also confirmed that ''Sanju'' will be released in [[China]].<ref>{{cite web |title=After crossing BO collection of over Rs 30 |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/after-crossing-bo-collection-of-over-rs-300-cr-sanju-to-win-over-china/articleshow/65071338.cms |website=economictimes.indiatimes.com |accessdate=22 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\n\n=== India ===\n''Sanju'' received mostly positive reviews from critics, with particular praise for Kapoor's performance and Hirani's direction.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/box-office-collection/sanju-box-office-collection-ranbir-kapoor-5238865/|title=Sanju box office collection day 1: Ranbir Kapoor's movie earns Rs 34.75 crore|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=1 July 2018|date=1 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629143423/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/box-office-collection/sanju-box-office-collection-ranbir-kapoor-5238865/|archivedate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/from-rockstar-to-sanju-how-ranbir-kapoors-experiments-as-an-actor-also-won-over-the-box-office-4636121.html|title=From Rockstar to Sanju, how Ranbir Kapoor's experiments as an actor also won over the box office|work=Firstpost|date=30 June 2018|last=Chintamani|first=Gautam|accessdate=30 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sanju review round-up: Critics give four stars out of five to the Ranbir Kapoor starrer|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sanju-review-round-this-what-critics-have-say-about-ranbir-kapoors-film-773435|publisher=International Business Times|last=Narayan|first=Shreya|date=29 June 2018|accessdate=1 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629123910/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sanju-review-round-this-what-critics-have-say-about-ranbir-kapoors-film-773435|archivedate=29 June 2018}}</ref> Swetha Ramakrishnan of ''[[Firstpost]]'' praised the performances of the cast, especially Kapoor, further writing, \"the film doesn't attempt to decode Sanjay Dutt or justify his life. Neither does it try to whitewash his flaws.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sanju-movie-review-ranbir-kapoor-is-flawless-in-rajkumar-hiranis-bollywood-ised-biopic-of-sanjay-dutt-4622211.html|title=Sanju: Ranbir Kapoor is flawless in Rajkumar Hirani's Bollywood-ised biopic of Sanjay Dutt- Entertainment News, Firstpost|publisher=|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref> [[Taran Adarsh]] of ''[[Bollywood Hungama]]'' gave the film four and a half stars out of five and writes, \"Sanju is an entertaining saga that blends emotions, humour and drama in adequate doses. It is powerful, engaging, emotional as well as compelling\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/sanju/critic-review/|title=Sanju Movie Review: Bollywood Hungama|date=29 June 2018|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=29 June 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629114919/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/sanju/critic-review/|archivedate=29 June 2018}}</ref> Meena Iyer of ''[[Daily News and Analysis]]'' similarly rated the film four and a half stars out of five, stating that \"it\u2019s an emotional roller-coaster that will give you the satisfaction of having read a bestseller.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Iyer |first1=Meena |title='Sanju' Review: Ranbir Kapoor's Sanjay Dutt biopic is an emotional roller coaster that plays out like a bestseller! |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/movie-reviews/report-sanju-review-ranbir-kapoor-s-sanjay-dutt-biopic-is-an-emotional-roller-coaster-that-unfolds-like-a-bestseller-2630988 |website=dnaindia.com |publisher=DNA India |accessdate=30 June 2018 |date=30 June 2018}}</ref> Divya Solgama of ''[[Bollywood Times]]'' gave the film 4.5/5 stars stating that \"Sanju\u2019 is an emotionally enriching experience which every cinema lover should witness\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Solgama |first1=Divya |title='SANJU' MOVIE REVIEW BY 'DIVYA SOLGAMA' \u2013 'AN EMOTIONALLY ENRICHING EXPERIENCE WORTH WITNESSING...' |url=http://www.bollywoodtimes.in/bt-exclusive/2/421/sanju-movie-review-by-divya-solgama-an-emotionally-enriching-experience-worth-witnessing |website=bollywoodtimes.in |accessdate=18 July 2018 |date=29 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nRachit Gupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' rated the film four stars out of five and commented, \"Whether he\u2019s dancing like a hysterical man under the influence of drugs or he\u2019s the broken, emotional wreck just staring blank, Ranbir portrays a variety of emotions and grey shades with flair.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/sanju/movie-review/64790325.cms|title=Sanju Review {4/5}: A spectacular and emotional look at the controversial life of Sanjay Dutt|publisher=|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref> Saibal Chatterjee of ''[[NDTV]]'' praised Kapoor's performance and Hirani's direction, but felt that \"other actors scramble to keep up\", especially Rawal. He concludes the review by writing, \"an absolute must-watch\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/sanju-movie-review-ranbir-kapoor-dazzles-as-sanjay-dutt-4-stars-out-of-5-1875187|title=Sanju Movie Review: Ranbir Kapoor Dazzles As Sanjay Dutt, Other Actors Scramble To Keep Up|publisher=|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref> A reviewer for ''[[India Today]]'' writes, \"Director Rajkumar Hirani, who has also co-written and edited Sanju, has taken more than a few dramatic liberties, but it feels refreshingly candid.\" He appreciates Kaushal as \"[holding] his own against Ranbir's superlative performance.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/reviews/story/sanju-movie-review-ranbir-kapoor-breathes-life-into-the-sanjay-dutt-biopic-1272911-2018-06-29|title=Sanju movie review: Ranbir Kapoor breathes life into Dutt biopic|website=India Today|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nDevesh Sharma of ''[[Filmfare]]'' appreciated the film's humour and applauded the writing as \"the strength of the film\". He notes, \"Sanju tells you superstars are humans too\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/reviews/bollywood-movies/sanju-movie-review-a-cracking-take-on-the-life-of-sanjay-dutt-29074.html|title=Movie Review: Sanju|publisher=|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref> Gaurang Chauhan of ''[[Times Now]]'' rated the film three and a half stars out of five. While criticising the background score and the first half, he praised the performances and second half of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/reviews/movies/article/sanju-movie-review-eccentric-story-of-a-flawed-sanjay-dutt-portrayed-by-a-brilliant-ranbir-kapoor/247493|title=Sanju Movie Review: If Ranbir Kapoor is the soul, Vicky Kaushal is the heart of this Sanjay Dutt biopic|publisher=|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref> Ankita Chakravarti of ''[[Zee News]]'' praised the performances of the ensemble cast stating that \"each and every cast is worth every attention\" as \"all the actors have done complete justice to their characters.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chakravarti |first1=Ankita |title=Sanju movie review: Ranbir Kapoor starrer is a collusion of emotions |url=http://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/sanju-moview-review-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-is-a-collusion-of-emotions-2121119.html |website=zeenews.india.com |publisher=Zee News |accessdate=29 June 2018 |date=29 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629115746/http://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/sanju-moview-review-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-is-a-collusion-of-emotions-2121119.html |archivedate=29 June 2018  }}</ref> [[Rajeev Masand]], writing for ''[[CNN-News18]]'', gave the film three and a half stars out of five, believing that the \"shrewd writing, and Ranbir Kapoor\u2019s extraordinary performance makes it hard not to empathize with the protagonist.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Sanju Review: Ranbir Kapoor-starrer is a Consistently Engaging Film|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/sanju-review-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-is-a-consistently-engaging-film-1795981.html|publisher=CNN-News18|last=Masand|first=Rajeev|date=30 June 2018|accessdate=1 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701083457/https://www.news18.com/news/movies/sanju-review-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-is-a-consistently-engaging-film-1795981.html|archivedate=1 July 2018}}{{Rating|3.5|5}}</ref> Rohit Bhatnagar of ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]'' labelled ''Sanju'' as \"enjoyable\", while noting that it tries to clear Dutt's image.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/290618/sanju-movie-review-ranbir-kapoor-rajkumar-hirani-anushka-vicky-manisha.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=29 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629104722/https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/290618/sanju-movie-review-ranbir-kapoor-rajkumar-hirani-anushka-vicky-manisha.html |archivedate=29 June 2018  }}</ref>\n\nUday Bhatia of ''[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]'' was critical of Dutt's portrayal, while mostly appreciating Kapoor's performance.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bhatia|first=Uday|url=https://www.livemint.com/Consumer/jA1MafVd2TiiZ0yhG1TsvO/Movie-Review-Sanju.html|title=Movie Review: 'Sanju'|accessdate=29 June 2018|date=29 June 2018|work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]}}</ref> Rohit Vats of ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' appreciated Kapoor's performance, but criticized the predictable nature of the script and songs which \"break the narrative\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Vats |first1=Rohit |title=Sanju movie review: Ranbir Kapoor shines in an indulgent Sanjay Dutt biopic |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sanju-movie-review-ratings-a-biopic-of-sanjay-dutt-ranbir-kapoor-anushka-sharma-manisha-koirala-sonam-kapoor/story-s3lMGYxx2TYD8Ie9BNSV7I.html |website=hindustantimes.com |publisher=Hindustan Times |accessdate=29 June 2018 |date=29 June 2018}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''Indian Express'' rated the film two and a half stars out of five, stating that \"Hirani is in top form getting all his reel characters to off the real characters, in the pursuit of a solid, entertaining tale\" but criticized the second half as to whether what had been left out of the film would have made it more better.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gupta |first1=Shubhra |title=Sanjay movie review: The Sanjay Dutt biopic is mostly engaging |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/sanju-movie-review-ranbir-kapoor-5238651/ |website=indianexpress.com |publisher=Indian Express |accessdate=29 June 2018 |date=29 June 2018}}</ref> [[Anna M. M. Vetticad]] of ''Firstpost'' described Kapoor's performance as \"superb\", but was unhappy with how \"startlingly dishonest\" the film was.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sanju-movie-review-ranbir-kapoor-is-superb-but-what-a-startlingly-dishonest-sanjay-dutt-biopic-this-is-4629331.html|title=Sanju movie review: Ranbir Kapoor is superb, but what a startlingly dishonest Sanjay Dutt biopic this is- Entertainment News, Firstpost|publisher=|accessdate=30 June 2018}}</ref> Nandini Ramanath of Scroll.in was impassive about the film, writing, \"In its relentless quest to offer absolution, ''Sanju'' is no better or worse than many other biopics that have flooded Bollywood over the past few years.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scroll.in/reel/884551/sanju-film-review-ranbir-kapoor-redeems-rajkumar-hiranis-fawning-sanjay-dutt-biopic|title=Ranbir Kapoor redeems Rajkumar Hirani's fawning Sanjay Dutt biopic|work=Scroll.in|date=29 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Overseas ===\n<!--Do NOT add Rotten Tomatoes rating here, per [[WP:Review aggregators]], \"However, if Rotten Tomatoes has a sample of 10 reviews for an independent film, the sample is not large enough for the score to be statistically accurate\".-->\nLisa Tsering of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' gave the film 3.5/5 and stated that whilst \"Sanju grabs the viewer's attention and delivers performances that glow long after the film is over\" felt that the film was \"a glorified infomercial about the life of a Bollywood bad boy.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tsering |first1=Lisa |title='Sanju': Film Review |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/sanju-review-1124321 |website=thehollywoodreporter.com |publisher=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=2 July 2018}}</ref> Similarly, Mike McCahill of ''[[The Guardian]]'' criticised how \"this three hour hagiography simply blames everyone else for his troubles\" though praised Kapoor for being \"a lightweight film\u2019s strongest suit\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=McCahill |first1=Mike |title=Sanju review \u2013 biopic of Bollywood bad boy Sanjay Dutt drowns in self-evasion |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/jun/29/sanju-review-bollywood-bad-boy-sanjay-dutt-self-evasion |website=theguardian.com |publisher=The Guardian |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=29 July 2018}}</ref> Shilpa Jamkhandikar of ''[[Reuters]]'' similarly praised Kapoor stating that what is \"bearable is Hirani\u2019s leading man and his chameleon-like ability to transform himself into various avatars\" and also criticized the script as it \"stretches too long and resorts to melodrama over substance\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jamkhandkikar |first1=Shilpa |title=Movie review Sanju |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/sanju-sanjay-dutt-hirani/movie-review-sanju-idUKKBN1JP2DG |website=ukreuters.com |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=29 June 2018}}</ref> Mary Gayen of ''The National'' however praised the film giving it 3.5/5 stars, stating that Hirani's \"direction is very matter of fact in relation to the incidents, but very thorough with the feelings expressed by the main characters.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gayen |first1=Mary |title=Film review: Sanju is an emotional tribute to the Dutts |url=https://www.thenational.ae/arts-culture/film/film-review-sanju-is-an-emotional-tribute-to-the-dutts-1.745400 |website=thenational.ae |publisher=The National |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=29 June 2018}}</ref> Vikran Mathur of ''American Bazaar'' also praised the film stating that the \"team has weaved Sanju\u2019s story together beautifully as a cinematic experience\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mathur |first1=Vikram |title=Nitin Adsul mulling biopic of Anandibai Gopalrao Joshi, the first US-educated woman physician from India November 20, 2017 Biopic of tennis legend Vijay Amritraj to be co-produced by his son September 15, 2017 Arjun Rampal unveils 'Daddy' trailer at Google headquarters, looks incredible as Arun Gawli June 16, 2017 Film review: 'Sanju' \u2013 'Khalnayak Nahin, Nayak Hoon Main' |url=https://www.americanbazaaronline.com/2018/07/03/film-review-sanju-khalnayak-nahin-nayak-hoon-main-434979/ |website=americanbazaaronline.com |publisher=American Bazaar Online |accessdate=13 July 2018 |date=3 July 2018}}</ref> Danish Lakdawaala of ''Dubai Desi'' gave the film 3.5/5 stars praising the \"very well written and entertaining screenplay packed with powerful performance\" but criticized it being \"like a propaganda film rather than a biopic, where audience is slapped with the key message through out which was to clear Sanjay Dutt\u2019s name.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lakdawalaa |first1=Danish |title=Sanju-Movie Review (3.5/5 Stars) |url=https://dubaidesireviews.blogspot.com/2018/07/sanju-movie-review-355-stars.html |website=dubaidesireviews.blogspot.com |accessdate=18 July 2018 |date=2 July 2018}}</ref> Divesh Mirchandani of ''C'est Le Cinema'' \nwrites that the \"biggest takeaway from the film is that the director chooses not to give a clean chit to his long time colleague, and offers no justification for the actor's missteps\"'' ''by giving the film 3/5 stars''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mirchandani |first1=Divesh |title=SANJU (2018) REVIEW |url=http://www.thecasualcinepunk.com/2018/06/sanju2018-review.html |website=thecasualcinepunk.com |accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Date of Ceremony\n!Awards\n!Category\n!Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |10 August 2018\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[Indian Film Festival of Melbourne]]\n|Best Film\n|''Sanju''\n|{{Won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iffm.com.au/nominees.html|title=Indian Film Festival Melbourne|website=www.iffm.com.au|access-date=13 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/iffm-2018-rajkumar-hirani-sanju-vicky-kaushal-5303862/|title=IFFM 2018: Rajkumar Hirani's Sanju wins big|website=indianexpress.com|access-date=13 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Director\n|[[Rajkumar Hirani]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|Best Actor\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Ranbir Kapoor]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|Vanguard Award\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|Best Supporting Performance (Male/Female)\n|[[Vicky Kaushal]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |16 March 2019\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[Asian Film Awards]]\n|Best Director\n|[[Rajkumar Hirani]]\n|{{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/asian-film-awards-2019-1428707-2019-01-11|title=Asian Film Awards 2019: Sanju gets nominated for best film. 2.0 in race for best visual effects|last=AngelesJanuary 11|first=IANS Los|last2=January 11|first2=2019UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-02-18|last3=Ist|first3=2019 15:36}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Actor\n|[[Ranbir Kapoor]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|[[Vicky Kaushal]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Screenplay\n|[[Rajkumar Hirani]], [[Abhijat Joshi]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Original Music\n|[[A. R. Rahman]], Rohan-Rohan, Vikram Montrose\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |19 March 2019\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|Best Film\n|''Sanju''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zeecineawards.com/zee-cinema-air-zee-cine-awards-2019-march/|title=Zee Cinema To Air Zee Cine Awards 2019 In March|date=2019-03-13|website=Zee Cine Awards|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Actor\n|[[Ranbir Kapoor]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|[[Vicky Kaushal]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" |[[64th Filmfare Awards|23 March 2019]]\n| rowspan=\"7\" |[[Filmfare Awards]]\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Film|Best Film]]\n|[[Vinod Chopra Films]], [[Rajkumar Hirani Films]] \u2013 [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]], [[Rajkumar Hirani]]\n|{{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"7\" | <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-2019/nominations|title=Filmfare Awards 2019 Nominations &#124; 64th Filmfare Awards 2019|website=filmfare.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Best Director Award|Best Director]]\n|Rajkumar Hirani\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n|[[Ranbir Kapoor]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n|[[Vicky Kaushal]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor|Best Actor (Critics)]]\n|Ranbir Kapoor\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Lyricist|Best Lyrics]]\n|Shekhar Astitva \u2013 \"Kar Har Maidaan Fateh\"\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Choreography|Best Choreography]]\n|[[Ganesh Acharya|Ganesh Archarya]] - \"Main Badhiya Tu Bhi Badhiya\"\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" |[[20th IIFA Awards | 18 September 2019]]\n| rowspan=\"7\" |[[IIFA Awards]]\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Film|Best Picture]]\n|[[Vinod Chopra Films]], [[Rajkumar Hirani Films]] \u2013 [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]], [[Rajkumar Hirani]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"7\" | <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/iifa-2019-nominations-list-out-andhadhun-bags-13-noms-raazi-and-padmaavat-get-10-noms-each/story-yC2gwp5oaIGxEHwVdS7GhN.html|title=IIFA 2019 nominations list out: Andhadhun bags 13 noms, Raazi and Padmaavat get 10 noms each|date=28 August 2019|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/iifa-2019-ayushmann-khurrana-s-andhadun-bags-13-nominations-raazi-and-padmaavat-receive-10-each-1592694-2019-08-28|title=IIFA 2019: Ayushmann Khurrana's Andhadun bags 13 nominations, Raazi and Padmaavat receive 10 each|agency=Ist|newspaper=India Today}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| Rajkumar Hirani\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| Ranbir Kapoor\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n| Vicky Kaushal\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Story|Best Story]]\n| Abhijat Joshi, Rajkumar Hirani\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Male Playback Singer]]\n| [[Sukhwinder Singh]] - Kar Har Maidan Fateh\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Female Playback Singer|Best Female Playback Singer]]\n| [[Sunidhi Chauhan]] - [[Main Badhiya Tu Bhi Badhiya]]\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|25em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Portal|India|Film|Bollywood}}\n*{{IMDb title|6452574}}\n*{{Rotten Tomatoes|sanju}}\n*{{Mojo title|sanju}}\n*[http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/sanju/ ''Sanju''] at [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n{{Rajkumar Hirani}}\n{{A. R. Rahman}}\n{{ZeeCineAwardBestFilm}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Rajkumar Hirani]]\n[[Category:Films scored by A. R. Rahman]]\n[[Category:Fox Star Studios films]]\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:Films about Bollywood]]\n[[Category:Films about actors]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of actors]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo: though\u2192through (title change confirmed)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sanju"}
{"title_page": "Yasmin Qureshi", "text_new": "{{short description|British Labour politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Yasmin Qureshi\n| image               = Official portrait of Yasmin Qureshi crop 2.jpg\n| honorific-prefix    = \n| honorific-suffix    = [[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|MP]]\n\n| office             = [[Department for International Development|Shadow Minister for International Development]]\n| leader             = [[Keir Starmer]]\n| predecessor        = [[Preet Gill]]\n| term_start        = 9 April 2020\n| term_end          =\n| successor          = \n| office1              = [[Ministry of Justice (United Kingdom)|Shadow Minister for Justice]]\n| leader1              = [[Jeremy Corbyn]]\n| predecessor1         = [[Andy Slaughter]]\n| successor1           = [[Karl Turner (British politician)|Karl Turner]] (Legal Aid)\n| term_start1          = 9 October 2016\n|term_end1      = 9 April 2020\n| office2             = [[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]]<br />for [[Bolton South East (UK Parliament constituency)|Bolton South East]]\n| parliament2         = \n| majority2           = 7,598 (18.7%)\n| predecessor2        = [[Brian Iddon|Dr Brian Iddon]]\n| successor2          = \n| term_start2         = 6 May 2010\n| term_end2           = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1963|7|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Gujrat City]], [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]]\n| nationality         = British\n| spouse              = \n| party               = [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| alma_mater          = [[Polytechnic of the South Bank]], [[University College London]]\n| occupation          = Member of Parliament\n| profession          = \n| religion            = [[Islam]]\n| signature           = \n| website             = {{url|http://yasminqureshi.org.uk}}\n| footnotes           = \n}}\n\n'''Yasmin Qureshi''' (born 5 July 1963)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/democracylive/hi/representatives/profiles/35869.stm |title=Yasmin Qureshi |work=Democracy Live |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808123522/http://news.bbc.co.uk/democracylive/hi/representatives/profiles/35869.stm |archive-date=8 August 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> is a British [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] [[politician]] and a [[barrister]] practising criminal law. She headed the criminal legal section of the UN Mission in Kosovo<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/may/07/general-election-female-muslim-mps|title=General election 2010: first female Muslim MPs elected|first1=Jo|last1=Adetunji|first2=Mark|last2=Tran|date=7 May 2010|publisher=|via=www.theguardian.com|access-date=18 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407070956/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/may/07/general-election-female-muslim-mps|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and was later appointed Director of the department of Judicial Administration there.<ref name=\"politics.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.politics.co.uk/reference/yasmin-qureshi|title=Yasmin Qureshi|website=politics.co.uk|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072849/https://www.politics.co.uk/reference/yasmin-qureshi|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She was elected as the [[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]] (MP) for [[Bolton South East (UK Parliament constituency)|Bolton South East]] in the [[2010 United Kingdom general election|May 2010 general election]].<ref name=first>{{cite news |title=General election 2010: first female Muslim MPs elected |accessdate=7 May 2010 |date=7 May 2010 |publisher=Guardian News and Media |work=guardian.co.uk |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/may/07/general-election-female-muslim-mps |first1=Jo |last1=Adetunji |first2=Mark |last2=Tran |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407070956/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/may/07/general-election-female-muslim-mps |archive-date=7 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She became Shadow Minister for International Development in April 2020.<ref> https://labourlist.org/2020/04/shadow-ministers-appointed-as-starmer-completes-frontbench/ </ref>\n\n==Early life==\nQureshi was born in [[Gujrat City]], Pakistan, and moved to Britain when she was nine. Her father was an engineer, and the family lived in [[Watford]].<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/the-first-asian-woman-mp-6941181.html |title=The first Asian woman MP? |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=27 February 2004 |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113231456/http://www.standard.co.uk/news/the-first-asian-woman-mp-6941181.html |archive-date=13 November 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She is the youngest of three children.\n\nShe attended what is now [[London South Bank University]], and graduated with a BA (Hons) Law degree before studying for and sitting her examinations for the Bar at the Council of Legal Education. She gained a Master of Laws at [[University College London]].<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite news | url=http://ukpolitics.telegraph.co.uk/Bolton+South+East/Yasmin+Qureshi | work=The Telegraph | title=Yasmin Qureshi | access-date=15 November 2010 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320124918/http://ukpolitics.telegraph.co.uk/Bolton+South+East/Yasmin+Qureshi | archive-date=20 March 2012 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Legal career==\nQureshi  began her legal career with the Crown Prosecution Service as an in-house barrister, prosecuting on behalf of the Crown in numerous criminal cases.<ref name=\"obv.org.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.obv.org.uk/our-communities/politicians-and-campaigners/mps/yasmin-qureshi-mp|title=Yasmin Qureshi MP (Labour) \u2013 OBV|website=www.obv.org.uk|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072908/https://www.obv.org.uk/our-communities/politicians-and-campaigners/mps/yasmin-qureshi-mp|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nShe headed the criminal legal section of the UN Mission in [[Kosovo]],<ref name=first /> and was selected as co-ordinator of the Criminal Legal Unit from 2000\u20132001.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yasminqureshi.org.uk/about|title=About|website=Yasmin Qureshi|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806173720/https://www.yasminqureshi.org.uk/about/|archive-date=6 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> This role involved analysing legal systems in Kosovo to identify their limitations, with a focus on issues including people trafficking, domestic violence etc. She was then appointed Director of the Department of Judicial Administration in Kosovo.<ref name=\"politics.co.uk\"/> This entailed working to ensure the proper administration and monitoring of courts, prosecutors and investigation of judges offices.\n\nShe then worked as a human rights advisor to the former London mayor [[Ken Livingstone]]<ref name=first /> from 2004 to 2008.<ref name=\"politics.co.uk\"/> Qureshi also chaired the Human Rights and Civil Liberties Working Group of the [[Association of Muslim Lawyers]] and was President of the Pakistan Club (UK).<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n\nQureshi has undertaken community work for over 20 years, working with local law centres and the Citizen Advice Bureau alongside her legal career.<ref name=\"obv.org.uk\"/>\n\n==Political career==\nAt the age of 16, Qureshi joined the Labour Party and became active in local politics.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=story_15-3-2004_pg7_25 |title=The return of the Native?: Gujrati lass gears up for UK polls |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023193450/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=story_15-3-2004_pg7_25 |publisher=Daily Times |date=15 March 2004 |archivedate=23 October 2012 }}</ref> She stood, unsuccessfully, for Labour in the London constituency of [[Brent East (UK Parliament constituency)|Brent East]] in 2005.<ref name=first /> She was elected at the [[2010 United Kingdom general election|2010 general election]] in the safe Labour seat of Bolton South East.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://menmedia.co.uk/manchestereveningnews/news/s/1014832_yasmin_aiming_for_double_first |title=Yasmin aiming for double first |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |first=Paul |last=Britton |date=29 August 2007 |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112203515/http://menmedia.co.uk/manchestereveningnews/news/s/1014832_yasmin_aiming_for_double_first |archive-date=12 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nShe was elected in 2010 with 18,782 votes and 47.4% of the vote<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130726162034/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2010.txt|title=Wayback Machine|date=26 July 2013|website=web.archive.org|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191101043205/https://web.archive.org/web/20130726162034/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2010.txt|archive-date=1 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and has since achieved higher vote tallies and vote proportions in the following elections with an improved majority of 25,676 votes and 60.7% of the vote in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2015.txt|title=Wayback Machine|date=17 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017112223/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2015.txt|archive-date=17 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/politics/constituencies/E14000579|title=Bolton South East parliamentary constituency \u2013 Election 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420180528/https://www.bbc.com/news/politics/constituencies/E14000579|archive-date=20 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2010 Qureshi, [[Rushanara Ali]] and [[Shabana Mahmood]], elected at the same time, became Britain's first female [[Muslim]] MPs. Qureshi is also the first woman to be elected as the Member of Parliament for Bolton South East.<ref name=first />\n\nQureshi has served on a number of Committees in her time in parliament. From her entry into parliament in 2010 until 2015 she was on the Justice Committee.<ref name=\"parliament.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924/election-results|title=Yasmin Qureshi MP|website=UK Parliament|access-date=7 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072842/https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924/election-results|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> From 2013 to 2015 she was part of the Home Affairs Committee. Following the 2015 election she was on the Foreign Affairs Committee. In early October 2016, Qureshi was appointed as a Shadow Minister for Justice by Labour leader [[Jeremy Corbyn]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2016-10-09/jeremy-corbyn-welcomes-10-returning-mps-to-shadow-team/|title=Jeremy Corbyn welcomes 10 returning MPs to shadow team|publisher=[[ITV News]]|date=9 October 2016|accessdate=9 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109021736/http://www.itv.com/news/2016-10-09/jeremy-corbyn-welcomes-10-returning-mps-to-shadow-team/|archive-date=9 November 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2014 to 2015 Qureshi was on the Committee scrutinising the High Speed Rail (HS2) project.<ref name=\"parliament.uk\"/> She sought to scrutinise impacts and costing of the controversial project in light of concerns over its slow progress and high cost. She stated that \"it is important that the Department for Transport and the Secretary of State address these concerns fully in order that people can have confidence in the HS2 project\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.infrastructure-intelligence.com/article/apr-2014/committee-named-scrutinise-hs2-after-parliament-approves-%C2%A342bn-scheme|title=Committee named to scrutinise HS2 after Parliament approves \u00a342bn scheme|website=Infrastructure Intelligence|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180809083042/http://www.infrastructure-intelligence.com/article/apr-2014/committee-named-scrutinise-hs2-after-parliament-approves-%C2%A342bn-scheme|archive-date=9 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and highlighted how the benefits of HS2 needed to be felt by those in the North as well as the South: \u201cthere needs to be clarity and transparency over value for money and the benefits to the rest of the country, not just London\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10665186.high-speed-rail-link-is-vital-to-the-north-say-bolton-mps/|title=High-speed rail link is 'vital to the north', say Bolton MPs|website=The Bolton News|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072854/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10665186.high-speed-rail-link-is-vital-to-the-north-say-bolton-mps/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Select Committees==\n\nPrior to taking up her position as Shadow Justice Minister, Qureshi sat on a variety of [[Select Committees]]. This included:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Select Committee !! House !! Date\n|-\n| Foreign Affairs Sub-Committee|| Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jan 2016 \u2013 Oct 2016]\n|-\n| Foreign Affairs Committee || Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jul 2015 \u2013 Oct 2016]\n|-\n| High Speed Rail (London \u2013 West Midlands) Bill || Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Apr 2014 \u2013 Jul 2015]\n|-\n| Home Affairs Committee || Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Nov 2013 \u2013 Mar 2015]\n|-\n| Privacy and Injunctions || Joint|| [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jul 2011 \u2013 Mar 2012]\n|-\n| Political and Constitutional Reform Committee || Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jul 2011 \u2013 Dec 2011]\n|-\n| Justice Committee|| Commons ||  [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jul 2010 \u2013 Mar 2015]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Parliamentary campaigns==\n\n===Primodos campaign===\nSince 2011, Qureshi has been campaigning for justice for the parents and children of those affected by Primodos, a historic hormone pregnancy test used in the 1960s and 1970s which significant evidence indicates leads to birth defects in children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2017/nov/15/1960s-hormone-pregnancy-test-did-not-cause-birth-defects-review-finds|title=Anger after report finds birth defects not caused by hormone pregnancy tests|first=Holly|last=Watt|date=15 November 2017|via=www.theguardian.com|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2017/nov/15/1960s-hormone-pregnancy-test-did-not-cause-birth-defects-review-finds|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/primodos-sky-news-exposes-pregnancy-drug-cover-up-10807338|title=Primodos: Sky News exposes pregnancy drug cover-up|website=Sky News|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072844/https://news.sky.com/story/primodos-sky-news-exposes-pregnancy-drug-cover-up-10807338|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She has worked to bring about an inquiry into a purported cover-up of information on the drug which may have taken place in the 1970s and 1980s.<ref name=\"auto\"/> In 2017 she stated in the House of Commons that a Report into Primodos had been \"condemned by MPs across the House as being a whitewash and misleading\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15680153.yasmin-qureshi-mp-condemns-whitewash-review-into-link-between-primodos-hormone-pregnancy-tests-and-birth-defects/|title=MP condemns 'whitewash' review into link between hormone pregnancy tests and birth defects|website=The Bolton News|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072902/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15680153.yasmin-qureshi-mp-condemns-whitewash-review-into-link-between-primodos-hormone-pregnancy-tests-and-birth-defects/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and called for a formal inquiry.\n\n===Community pharmacies===\n\nQureshihas also campaigned against cuts to community pharmacies. Speaking in 2016 she stated that \u201ccutting funding for community pharmacies threatens patient care and safety\" <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14505919.mp-urges-bolton-residents-to-support-local-pharmacies-as-170-million-cuts-loom/|title=MP urges Bolton residents to support local pharmacies as \u00a3170 million cuts loom|work=[[The Bolton News]]|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072901/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14505919.mp-urges-bolton-residents-to-support-local-pharmacies-as-170-million-cuts-loom/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and that \"pharmacies are vital local assets and these cuts are totally short-sighted\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14847210.mp-hits-out-over-pharmacy-closures/|title=MP hits out over pharmacy closures|work=[[The Bolton News]]|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072857/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14847210.mp-hits-out-over-pharmacy-closures/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Rohingya crisis===\n\nIn response to the Myanmar's Rohingya crisis Qureshi has called for the government to condemn the crisis and work more with the international community to seek a rapid end to it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41163651|title=UK MPs: Help fleeing Rohingya Muslims|date=5 September 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418123603/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41163651|archive-date=18 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She commented that \"this is one of the worst outbreaks of violence in decades, yet the international community is effectively remaining silent as we watch another Srebrenica and Rwanda unfold before our eyes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15518150.yasmin-qureshi-mp-calls-for-action-on-ethnic-cleansing-in-burma/|title=MP calls for action on 'ethnic cleansing' in Burma|website=The Bolton News|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072852/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15518150.yasmin-qureshi-mp-calls-for-action-on-ethnic-cleansing-in-burma/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Upskirting bill===\n\nQureshi campaigned extensively to have 'upskirting' criminalised as a specific sexual offence, arguing that such legislation was long overdue. In response to Conservative MP Christopher Chope's blocking the progress of a bill to outlaw upskirting, Qureshi spoke frequently in the House of Commons in criticism of this action, stating: \"delays in getting to this point were totally unnecessary and have caused needless suffering\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-06-18/debates/5D764E22-1EFB-4F49-89C7-86AD375DFE9D/Upskirting#contribution-86AD4442-EBD9-46C2-9336-6EC8D6CB91CD|title=Upskirting \u2013 Hansard|website=hansard.parliament.uk|access-date=17 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180717183434/https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-06-18/debates/5D764E22-1EFB-4F49-89C7-86AD375DFE9D/Upskirting#contribution-86AD4442-EBD9-46C2-9336-6EC8D6CB91CD|archive-date=17 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Other campaigns===\n\nQureshi has also supported a number of other campaigns while in parliament. These include seeking to reduce the impacts of changes in State Pension Age,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/YasminQureshiMP/status/774277812287045632|title=Join us next Friday in Manchester & stand shoulder to shoulder with #WASPI women who face an unfair pension age hikepic.twitter.com/VGSHnTSBs0|first=Yasmin Qureshi|last=MP|date=9 September 2016|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190913170817/https://twitter.com/YasminQureshiMP/status/774277812287045632|archive-date=13 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2017/04/labour-targets-older-voters-pensioner-s-pledge-card|title=Labour targets older voters with Pensioner's Pledge Card|website=www.newstatesman.com|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806175539/https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2017/04/labour-targets-older-voters-pensioner-s-pledge-card|archive-date=6 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> calls for citizens to be able to opt-out of unsolicited phone calls from companies,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.yasminqureshi.org.uk/mp_welcomes_mobile_nuisance_calls_opt_out_full_release|title=MP welcomes mobile nuisance calls opt out \u2013 Yasmin Qureshi MP|date=28 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180228041307/http://www.yasminqureshi.org.uk/mp_welcomes_mobile_nuisance_calls_opt_out_full_release|archive-date=28 February 2018}}</ref> and questioning the pace of government cuts and the effect this is having on crime and local communities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15917908.mp-writes-to-home-secretary-about-rising-crime-concerns/|title=MP writes to Home Secretary about rising crime concerns|website=The Bolton News|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072855/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15917908.mp-writes-to-home-secretary-about-rising-crime-concerns/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Parliamentary Groups==\n\nShe is currently involved with a number of All Party Parliamentary Groups ([[All-party parliamentary group|APPG]]).\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! APPG !! Role\n|-\n| India || Treasurer\n|-\n| Pakistan || Secretary\n|-\n| Palestine || Vice Chair\n|-\n| Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus || Chair and Registered Contact\n|-\n| Chess || Chair & Registered Contact\n|-\n| Childcare and Early Education || Officer\n|-\n| Communities Engagement || Secretary\n|-\n| Dalit || Chair & Registered Contact\n|-\n| Dentistry and Oral Health || Vice Chair\n|-\n| Domestic Abuse || Vice Chair\n|-\n| Greater Manchester || Treasurer\n|-\n| Hajj and Umrah || Chair & Registered Contact\n|-\n| Hormone Pregnancy Tests || Chair & Registered Contact\n|-\n| Kidney || Vice Chair<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/190213/register-190213.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=25 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072842/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/190213/register-190213.pdf |archive-date=7 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n'''APPG for Srebenica''':<ref name=\"publications.parliament.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/170329/srebrenica.htm|title=House of Commons \u2013 Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 29 March 2017: Srebrenica|website=publications.parliament.uk|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180227213740/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/170329/srebrenica.htm|archive-date=27 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Qureshi chairs this group. It seeks to \"increase awareness of the Srebrenica genocide and institutionalise 11 July in the UK as Srebrenica Memorial Day in line with the 2009 resolution of the European Parliament as the best means of honouring the victims, sending a clear message to future generations and stressing the importance of reconciliation as part of the European integration process\".<ref name=\"publications.parliament.uk\"/>\n\n'''APPG for Religion in the Media''' :\nQureshi set up and chairs this APPG. It aims to open dialogues about depictions of religion in the media, in the hope of \"fostering a better understanding and representation of religion in the media as religion is a prime motivator of individuals and the community\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160721/religion-in-the-media.htm|title=House of Commons \u2013 Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 21 July 2016: Religion in the Media|website=publications.parliament.uk|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160721/religion-in-the-media.htm|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n'''APPG for Chess''':\nQureshi chairs this group, which seeks to \"publicise, promote and seek support for Chess\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160203/chess.htm|title=House of Commons \u2013 Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 3 February 2016: Chess|website=publications.parliament.uk|access-date=7 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072846/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160203/chess.htm|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Based on the findings that playing chess helps improve children's concentration and focus, the APPG seeks to have chess recognised as a sport and expand the opportunities for primary and secondary school students to play chess.\n\n'''APPG on Hormone Pregnancy Tests''':\nQureshi chairs this APPG and is its point of contact. It seeks to investigate the adverse effects of Primodos (please see sub-section above).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160203/oral-hormone-pregnancy-tests.htm|title=House of Commons \u2013 Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 3 February 2016: Oral Hormone Pregnancy Tests|website=publications.parliament.uk|access-date=7 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160203/oral-hormone-pregnancy-tests.htm|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n'''APPG for Dentistry and Oral Health''':\nQureshi is the Vice-Chair of this APPG. It acts as a \"forum for dental and oral health issues in Parliament, and works to raise the profile of dentistry, highlighting the views of both patients and the profession\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appgdentistry.org/|title=APPG Dentistry & Oral Health \u2013 Home|website=www.appgdentistry.org|access-date=7 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407074349/http://www.appgdentistry.org/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appgdentistry.org/Membership|title=APPG Dentistry & Oral Health \u2013 Membership|website=www.appgdentistry.org|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072854/http://www.appgdentistry.org/Membership|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2019 she wrote to Health Secretary Matt Hancock urging him to act to deal with what she described as a 'crisis in dentistry'.<ref name=\"dentistry.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dentistry.co.uk/2019/02/12/yasmin-qureshi-mp-urges-government-action-nhs-dentistry/|title=Yasmin Qureshi MP urges government for action on NHS dentistry|date=12 February 2019|via=www.dentistry.co.uk|access-date=25 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://www.dentistry.co.uk/2019/02/12/yasmin-qureshi-mp-urges-government-action-nhs-dentistry/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The letter was co-signed by 16 other Labour MPs.<ref name=\"dentistry.co.uk\"/>\n\n==Political positions==\n\n===Court building sales===\n\nQureshi has been a stringent critic of the widespread closure of courts and sales of court buildings throughout her time as an MP. She argues that doing so without due process and in a rushed manner \"piles yet more pressure on the remaining courts and risks hearings being further delayed and rescheduled\", with the impact of \"distressing victims and witnesses, many of whom are now forced to travel much greater distances\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://labourlist.org/2018/06/yasmin-qureshi-our-justice-system-is-being-brought-to-its-knees-by-tory-cuts/|title=Yasmin Qureshi: Our justice system is being brought to its knees by Tory cuts|date=21 June 2018|accessdate=26 February 2019|first=Yasmin|last=Qureshi|website=LabourList.org|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404225520/https://labourlist.org/2018/06/yasmin-qureshi-our-justice-system-is-being-brought-to-its-knees-by-tory-cuts/|archive-date=4 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Prison system===\n\nQureshi has been a consistent critique of the Conservatives running of the prison system. In the Huffington Post she argued that the 14% rate of prison officers leaving after a year, the record rates of prisoner suicides and the increasing safety crisis as noted by inspections indicate that prison funding and staff numbers had been cut too rapidly.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/yasmin-qureshi/prison-suicide-rates_b_13283674.html|title=Record Suicide Figures Prove That, Under This Government, The Prison System Is Broken|date=28 November 2016|website=HuffPost UK|access-date=17 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180717154246/https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/yasmin-qureshi/prison-suicide-rates_b_13283674.html|archive-date=17 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Syrian bombing===\n\nQureshi was strongly against the dropping of bombs in [[Syria]]; after travelling on a fact-finding mission with the Foreign Affairs Committee, she argued that while the bombs would certainly cause \"many innocent civilian deaths\", the evidence that the strikes would significantly weaken ISIS was unclear.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14118859.bolton-mp-yasmin-qureshi-makes-final-bid-to-prevent-uk-from-bombing-syria-during-house-of-commons-debate/|title=Bolton MP Yasmin Qureshi makes final bid to prevent UK from bombing Syria during House of Commons debate|website=The Bolton News|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072903/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14118859.bolton-mp-yasmin-qureshi-makes-final-bid-to-prevent-uk-from-bombing-syria-during-house-of-commons-debate/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-34987921|title=Syria strikes: Find out how your MP voted|date=3 December 2015|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416185933/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-34987921|archive-date=16 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\nIn January 2013 and 2015, Qureshi was nominated for the Politician of the Year award at the [[British Muslim Awards]].<ref name=\"asianimage1\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/10197507.Winners_honoured_at_British_Muslim_Awards/|title=Winners honoured at British Muslim Awards|work=|location=|publisher=Asian Image|date=31 January 2013|accessdate=1 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151121173521/http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/10197507.Winners_honoured_at_British_Muslim_Awards/|archive-date=21 November 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"asianimage3\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/business/11745550.British_Muslim_Awards_2015_finalists_unveiled/|title=British Muslim Awards 2015 finalists unveiled|work=|location=|publisher=Asian Image|date=23 January 2015|accessdate=1 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150730005602/http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/business/11745550.British_Muslim_Awards_2015_finalists_unveiled/|archive-date=30 July 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2014, she was awarded the Politician of the Year award at the British Muslim Awards.<ref name=\"asianimage2\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/united_kingdom/10978079.British_Muslim_Awards_2014_winners/|title=British Muslim Awards 2014 winners|work=|location=|publisher=Asian Image|date=31 January 2014|accessdate=1 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151122185051/http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/united_kingdom/10978079.British_Muslim_Awards_2014_winners/|archive-date=22 November 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Other activities==\nIn February 2014, during a parliamentary debate on the Palestine crisis, she said of the persecution of Jewish people in [[the Holocaust]]: \"Their properties, homes, and land\u2014everything\u2014were taken away, and they were deprived of rights. Of course, many millions perished\", before going on to say that \"It is quite strange that some of the people who are running the state of Israel seem to be quite complacent and happy to allow the same to happen in Gaza\". In response, Karen Pollock of the [[Holocaust Educational Trust]] said: \"We expect our politicians to speak responsibly and sensitively about the past and about events today. These lazy and deliberate distortions have no place in British politics\". Qureshi apologised to any who were offended by her words, and stated that \"the debate was about the plight of the Palestinian people, and in no way did I mean to equate events in Gaza with the Holocaust\", adding that \"I know the Holocaust was the most brutal act of genocide of the 20th century, and no one should seek to underestimate its impact\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/feb/07/labour-mp-apologises-holocaust-remark|title=Labour MP apologises for Holocaust remark|work=The Guardian|agency=Press Association|date=7 February 2014|accessdate=10 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317171354/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/feb/07/labour-mp-apologises-holocaust-remark|archive-date=17 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Dysch|first=Marcus|url=http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/115505/labour-mp-yasmin-qureshi-apologises-gaza-holocaust-comparison|title=Labour MP Yasmin Qureshi apologises for Gaza-Holocaust comparison|work=The Jewish Chronicle|date=10 February 2014|accessdate=10 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011065610/http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/115505/labour-mp-yasmin-qureshi-apologises-gaza-holocaust-comparison|archive-date=11 October 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/feb/07/labour-mp-apologises-holocaust-remark|title=Labour MP apologises for Holocaust remark|first=Press|last=Association|date=7 February 2014|via=www.theguardian.com|access-date=10 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317171354/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/feb/07/labour-mp-apologises-holocaust-remark|archive-date=17 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, Qureshi opposed mandatory labelling of meat coming from animals killed by [[Dhabihah|halal]] and [[Shechita|kosher]] methods. She drew attention to studies which indicated that halal methods of slaughtering may not be more painful than stunning, saying \"a myth is being perpetuated that somehow kosher and halal methods, carried out as they should be, are more painful and cause more suffering to the animal, but that is incorrect\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.politics.co.uk/news/2014/05/14/mps-block-compulsory-halal-meat-labelling |title=MPs block compulsory halal meat labelling |publisher=politics.co.uk |first=Adam |last=Bienkov |date=14 May 2014 |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707201144/http://www.politics.co.uk/news/2014/05/14/mps-block-compulsory-halal-meat-labelling |archive-date=7 July 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2014-05-13a.654.0 |title=Right to supply tickets to events of national significance |publisher=TheyWorkForYou |date=13 May 2014 |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808150050/http://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2014-05-13a.654.0 |archive-date=8 August 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, ''[[The Times]]'' stated that Qureshi accepted a \u00a35,000 donation from [[Sufyan Ismail]] but failed to declare it;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/extremist-leads-muslim-lobby-group-7q2hg30zc|title=Extremist leads Muslim lobby group|first=Dominic Kennedy|last=Investigations\u00a0Editor|date=10 April 2017|publisher=|via=www.thetimes.co.uk|access-date=7 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/extremist-leads-muslim-lobby-group-7q2hg30zc|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> it was found that the donation was in fact declared on time and in keeping with parliamentary procedure, it was declared through Ismail's company name 'One Group' and can be found on public parliamentary donation records.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmregmem/150713/150713.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=17 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121030125/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmregmem/150713/150713.pdf |archive-date=21 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Qureshi was banned from driving for 6 months for driving without insurance and using a mobile phone, whilst already having 9 points.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-manchester-11027669|title=Bolton MP is banned from driving|date=19 August 2010|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416181332/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-manchester-11027669|archive-date=16 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://yasminqureshi.org.uk/ Yasmin Qureshi MP] Official constituency website\n*{{UK MP links | parliament = yasmin-qureshi/3924 | guardian = 8667/yasmin-qureshi | publicwhip = Yasmin_Qureshi | theywork = yasmin_qureshi | record = Yasmin-Qureshi/Bolton-South-East/1150 | bbc = 35869.stm | journalisted = }}\n* {{C-SPAN|yasminqureshi}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|uk}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Brian Iddon]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|[[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]] for [[Bolton South East (UK Parliament constituency)|Bolton South East]]}}|years=[[2010 United Kingdom general election|2010]]\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{North West Labour Party MPs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Qureshi, Yasmin}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of London South Bank University]]\n[[Category:British politicians of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:British Muslims]]\n[[Category:Female members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Labour Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Pakistani emigrants to the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Naturalised citizens of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:British people of Punjabi descent]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2010\u20132015]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2015\u20132017]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2017\u20132019]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2019\u2013]]\n[[Category:21st-century British women politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for Bolton South East]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British Labour politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Yasmin Qureshi\n| image               = Official portrait of Yasmin Qureshi crop 2.jpg\n| honorific-prefix    = \n| honorific-suffix    = [[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|MP]]\n\n| office             = [[Department for International Development|Shadow Minister for International Development]]\n| leader             = [[Keir Starmer]]\n| predecessor        = [[Preet Gill]]\n| term_start        = 9 April 2020\n| term_end          =\n| successor          = \n| office1              = [[Ministry of Justice (United Kingdom)|Shadow Minister for Justice]]\n| leader1              = [[Jeremy Corbyn]]\n| predecessor1         = [[Andy Slaughter]]\n| successor1           = [[Karl Turner]] (Legal Aid)\n| term_start1          = 9 October 2016\n|term_end1      = 9 April 2020\n| office2             = [[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]]<br />for [[Bolton South East (UK Parliament constituency)|Bolton South East]]\n| parliament2         = \n| majority2           = 7,598 (18.7%)\n| predecessor2        = [[Brian Iddon|Dr Brian Iddon]]\n| successor2          = \n| term_start2         = 6 May 2010\n| term_end2           = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1963|7|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Gujrat City]], [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]]\n| nationality         = British\n| spouse              = \n| party               = [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| alma_mater          = [[Polytechnic of the South Bank]], [[University College London]]\n| occupation          = Member of Parliament\n| profession          = \n| religion            = [[Islam]]\n| signature           = \n| website             = {{url|http://yasminqureshi.org.uk}}\n| footnotes           = \n}}\n\n'''Yasmin Qureshi''' (born 5 July 1963)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/democracylive/hi/representatives/profiles/35869.stm |title=Yasmin Qureshi |work=Democracy Live |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808123522/http://news.bbc.co.uk/democracylive/hi/representatives/profiles/35869.stm |archive-date=8 August 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> is a British [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] [[politician]] and a [[barrister]] practising criminal law. She headed the criminal legal section of the UN Mission in Kosovo<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/may/07/general-election-female-muslim-mps|title=General election 2010: first female Muslim MPs elected|first1=Jo|last1=Adetunji|first2=Mark|last2=Tran|date=7 May 2010|publisher=|via=www.theguardian.com|access-date=18 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407070956/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/may/07/general-election-female-muslim-mps|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and was later appointed Director of the department of Judicial Administration there.<ref name=\"politics.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.politics.co.uk/reference/yasmin-qureshi|title=Yasmin Qureshi|website=politics.co.uk|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072849/https://www.politics.co.uk/reference/yasmin-qureshi|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She was elected as the [[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]] (MP) for [[Bolton South East (UK Parliament constituency)|Bolton South East]] in the [[2010 United Kingdom general election|May 2010 general election]].<ref name=first>{{cite news |title=General election 2010: first female Muslim MPs elected |accessdate=7 May 2010 |date=7 May 2010 |publisher=Guardian News and Media |work=guardian.co.uk |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/may/07/general-election-female-muslim-mps |first1=Jo |last1=Adetunji |first2=Mark |last2=Tran |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407070956/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/may/07/general-election-female-muslim-mps |archive-date=7 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She became Shadow Minister for International Development in April 2020.<ref> https://labourlist.org/2020/04/shadow-ministers-appointed-as-starmer-completes-frontbench/ </ref>\n\n==Early life==\nQureshi was born in [[Gujrat City]], Pakistan, and moved to Britain when she was nine. Her father was an engineer, and the family lived in [[Watford]].<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/the-first-asian-woman-mp-6941181.html |title=The first Asian woman MP? |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=27 February 2004 |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113231456/http://www.standard.co.uk/news/the-first-asian-woman-mp-6941181.html |archive-date=13 November 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She is the youngest of three children.\n\nShe attended what is now [[London South Bank University]], and graduated with a BA (Hons) Law degree before studying for and sitting her examinations for the Bar at the Council of Legal Education. She gained a Master of Laws at [[University College London]].<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite news | url=http://ukpolitics.telegraph.co.uk/Bolton+South+East/Yasmin+Qureshi | work=The Telegraph | title=Yasmin Qureshi | access-date=15 November 2010 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320124918/http://ukpolitics.telegraph.co.uk/Bolton+South+East/Yasmin+Qureshi | archive-date=20 March 2012 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Legal career==\nQureshi  began her legal career with the Crown Prosecution Service as an in-house barrister, prosecuting on behalf of the Crown in numerous criminal cases.<ref name=\"obv.org.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.obv.org.uk/our-communities/politicians-and-campaigners/mps/yasmin-qureshi-mp|title=Yasmin Qureshi MP (Labour) \u2013 OBV|website=www.obv.org.uk|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072908/https://www.obv.org.uk/our-communities/politicians-and-campaigners/mps/yasmin-qureshi-mp|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nShe headed the criminal legal section of the UN Mission in [[Kosovo]],<ref name=first /> and was selected as co-ordinator of the Criminal Legal Unit from 2000\u20132001.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yasminqureshi.org.uk/about|title=About|website=Yasmin Qureshi|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806173720/https://www.yasminqureshi.org.uk/about/|archive-date=6 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> This role involved analysing legal systems in Kosovo to identify their limitations, with a focus on issues including people trafficking, domestic violence etc. She was then appointed Director of the Department of Judicial Administration in Kosovo.<ref name=\"politics.co.uk\"/> This entailed working to ensure the proper administration and monitoring of courts, prosecutors and investigation of judges offices.\n\nShe then worked as a human rights advisor to the former London mayor [[Ken Livingstone]]<ref name=first /> from 2004 to 2008.<ref name=\"politics.co.uk\"/> Qureshi also chaired the Human Rights and Civil Liberties Working Group of the [[Association of Muslim Lawyers]] and was President of the Pakistan Club (UK).<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n\nQureshi has undertaken community work for over 20 years, working with local law centres and the Citizen Advice Bureau alongside her legal career.<ref name=\"obv.org.uk\"/>\n\n==Political career==\nAt the age of 16, Qureshi joined the Labour Party and became active in local politics.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=story_15-3-2004_pg7_25 |title=The return of the Native?: Gujrati lass gears up for UK polls |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023193450/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=story_15-3-2004_pg7_25 |publisher=Daily Times |date=15 March 2004 |archivedate=23 October 2012 }}</ref> She stood, unsuccessfully, for Labour in the London constituency of [[Brent East (UK Parliament constituency)|Brent East]] in 2005.<ref name=first /> She was elected at the [[2010 United Kingdom general election|2010 general election]] in the safe Labour seat of Bolton South East.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://menmedia.co.uk/manchestereveningnews/news/s/1014832_yasmin_aiming_for_double_first |title=Yasmin aiming for double first |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |first=Paul |last=Britton |date=29 August 2007 |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112203515/http://menmedia.co.uk/manchestereveningnews/news/s/1014832_yasmin_aiming_for_double_first |archive-date=12 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nShe was elected in 2010 with 18,782 votes and 47.4% of the vote<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130726162034/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2010.txt|title=Wayback Machine|date=26 July 2013|website=web.archive.org|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191101043205/https://web.archive.org/web/20130726162034/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2010.txt|archive-date=1 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and has since achieved higher vote tallies and vote proportions in the following elections with an improved majority of 25,676 votes and 60.7% of the vote in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2015.txt|title=Wayback Machine|date=17 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017112223/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2015.txt|archive-date=17 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/politics/constituencies/E14000579|title=Bolton South East parliamentary constituency \u2013 Election 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420180528/https://www.bbc.com/news/politics/constituencies/E14000579|archive-date=20 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2010 Qureshi, [[Rushanara Ali]] and [[Shabana Mahmood]], elected at the same time, became Britain's first female [[Muslim]] MPs. Qureshi is also the first woman to be elected as the Member of Parliament for Bolton South East.<ref name=first />\n\nQureshi has served on a number of Committees in her time in parliament. From her entry into parliament in 2010 until 2015 she was on the Justice Committee.<ref name=\"parliament.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924/election-results|title=Yasmin Qureshi MP|website=UK Parliament|access-date=7 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072842/https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924/election-results|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> From 2013 to 2015 she was part of the Home Affairs Committee. Following the 2015 election she was on the Foreign Affairs Committee. In early October 2016, Qureshi was appointed as a Shadow Minister for Justice by Labour leader [[Jeremy Corbyn]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2016-10-09/jeremy-corbyn-welcomes-10-returning-mps-to-shadow-team/|title=Jeremy Corbyn welcomes 10 returning MPs to shadow team|publisher=[[ITV News]]|date=9 October 2016|accessdate=9 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109021736/http://www.itv.com/news/2016-10-09/jeremy-corbyn-welcomes-10-returning-mps-to-shadow-team/|archive-date=9 November 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2014 to 2015 Qureshi was on the Committee scrutinising the High Speed Rail (HS2) project.<ref name=\"parliament.uk\"/> She sought to scrutinise impacts and costing of the controversial project in light of concerns over its slow progress and high cost. She stated that \"it is important that the Department for Transport and the Secretary of State address these concerns fully in order that people can have confidence in the HS2 project\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.infrastructure-intelligence.com/article/apr-2014/committee-named-scrutinise-hs2-after-parliament-approves-%C2%A342bn-scheme|title=Committee named to scrutinise HS2 after Parliament approves \u00a342bn scheme|website=Infrastructure Intelligence|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180809083042/http://www.infrastructure-intelligence.com/article/apr-2014/committee-named-scrutinise-hs2-after-parliament-approves-%C2%A342bn-scheme|archive-date=9 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and highlighted how the benefits of HS2 needed to be felt by those in the North as well as the South: \u201cthere needs to be clarity and transparency over value for money and the benefits to the rest of the country, not just London\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10665186.high-speed-rail-link-is-vital-to-the-north-say-bolton-mps/|title=High-speed rail link is 'vital to the north', say Bolton MPs|website=The Bolton News|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072854/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10665186.high-speed-rail-link-is-vital-to-the-north-say-bolton-mps/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Select Committees==\n\nPrior to taking up her position as Shadow Justice Minister, Qureshi sat on a variety of [[Select Committees]]. This included:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Select Committee !! House !! Date\n|-\n| Foreign Affairs Sub-Committee|| Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jan 2016 \u2013 Oct 2016]\n|-\n| Foreign Affairs Committee || Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jul 2015 \u2013 Oct 2016]\n|-\n| High Speed Rail (London \u2013 West Midlands) Bill || Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Apr 2014 \u2013 Jul 2015]\n|-\n| Home Affairs Committee || Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Nov 2013 \u2013 Mar 2015]\n|-\n| Privacy and Injunctions || Joint|| [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jul 2011 \u2013 Mar 2012]\n|-\n| Political and Constitutional Reform Committee || Commons || [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jul 2011 \u2013 Dec 2011]\n|-\n| Justice Committee|| Commons ||  [https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/yasmin-qureshi/3924 Jul 2010 \u2013 Mar 2015]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Parliamentary campaigns==\n\n===Primodos campaign===\nSince 2011, Qureshi has been campaigning for justice for the parents and children of those affected by Primodos, a historic hormone pregnancy test used in the 1960s and 1970s which significant evidence indicates leads to birth defects in children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2017/nov/15/1960s-hormone-pregnancy-test-did-not-cause-birth-defects-review-finds|title=Anger after report finds birth defects not caused by hormone pregnancy tests|first=Holly|last=Watt|date=15 November 2017|via=www.theguardian.com|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2017/nov/15/1960s-hormone-pregnancy-test-did-not-cause-birth-defects-review-finds|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/primodos-sky-news-exposes-pregnancy-drug-cover-up-10807338|title=Primodos: Sky News exposes pregnancy drug cover-up|website=Sky News|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072844/https://news.sky.com/story/primodos-sky-news-exposes-pregnancy-drug-cover-up-10807338|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She has worked to bring about an inquiry into a purported cover-up of information on the drug which may have taken place in the 1970s and 1980s.<ref name=\"auto\"/> In 2017 she stated in the House of Commons that a Report into Primodos had been \"condemned by MPs across the House as being a whitewash and misleading\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15680153.yasmin-qureshi-mp-condemns-whitewash-review-into-link-between-primodos-hormone-pregnancy-tests-and-birth-defects/|title=MP condemns 'whitewash' review into link between hormone pregnancy tests and birth defects|website=The Bolton News|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072902/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15680153.yasmin-qureshi-mp-condemns-whitewash-review-into-link-between-primodos-hormone-pregnancy-tests-and-birth-defects/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and called for a formal inquiry.\n\n===Community pharmacies===\n\nQureshihas also campaigned against cuts to community pharmacies. Speaking in 2016 she stated that \u201ccutting funding for community pharmacies threatens patient care and safety\" <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14505919.mp-urges-bolton-residents-to-support-local-pharmacies-as-170-million-cuts-loom/|title=MP urges Bolton residents to support local pharmacies as \u00a3170 million cuts loom|work=[[The Bolton News]]|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072901/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14505919.mp-urges-bolton-residents-to-support-local-pharmacies-as-170-million-cuts-loom/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and that \"pharmacies are vital local assets and these cuts are totally short-sighted\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14847210.mp-hits-out-over-pharmacy-closures/|title=MP hits out over pharmacy closures|work=[[The Bolton News]]|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072857/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14847210.mp-hits-out-over-pharmacy-closures/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Rohingya crisis===\n\nIn response to the Myanmar's Rohingya crisis Qureshi has called for the government to condemn the crisis and work more with the international community to seek a rapid end to it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41163651|title=UK MPs: Help fleeing Rohingya Muslims|date=5 September 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418123603/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41163651|archive-date=18 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She commented that \"this is one of the worst outbreaks of violence in decades, yet the international community is effectively remaining silent as we watch another Srebrenica and Rwanda unfold before our eyes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15518150.yasmin-qureshi-mp-calls-for-action-on-ethnic-cleansing-in-burma/|title=MP calls for action on 'ethnic cleansing' in Burma|website=The Bolton News|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072852/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15518150.yasmin-qureshi-mp-calls-for-action-on-ethnic-cleansing-in-burma/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Upskirting bill===\n\nQureshi campaigned extensively to have 'upskirting' criminalised as a specific sexual offence, arguing that such legislation was long overdue. In response to Conservative MP Christopher Chope's blocking the progress of a bill to outlaw upskirting, Qureshi spoke frequently in the House of Commons in criticism of this action, stating: \"delays in getting to this point were totally unnecessary and have caused needless suffering\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-06-18/debates/5D764E22-1EFB-4F49-89C7-86AD375DFE9D/Upskirting#contribution-86AD4442-EBD9-46C2-9336-6EC8D6CB91CD|title=Upskirting \u2013 Hansard|website=hansard.parliament.uk|access-date=17 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180717183434/https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-06-18/debates/5D764E22-1EFB-4F49-89C7-86AD375DFE9D/Upskirting#contribution-86AD4442-EBD9-46C2-9336-6EC8D6CB91CD|archive-date=17 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Other campaigns===\n\nQureshi has also supported a number of other campaigns while in parliament. These include seeking to reduce the impacts of changes in State Pension Age,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/YasminQureshiMP/status/774277812287045632|title=Join us next Friday in Manchester & stand shoulder to shoulder with #WASPI women who face an unfair pension age hikepic.twitter.com/VGSHnTSBs0|first=Yasmin Qureshi|last=MP|date=9 September 2016|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190913170817/https://twitter.com/YasminQureshiMP/status/774277812287045632|archive-date=13 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2017/04/labour-targets-older-voters-pensioner-s-pledge-card|title=Labour targets older voters with Pensioner's Pledge Card|website=www.newstatesman.com|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806175539/https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2017/04/labour-targets-older-voters-pensioner-s-pledge-card|archive-date=6 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> calls for citizens to be able to opt-out of unsolicited phone calls from companies,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.yasminqureshi.org.uk/mp_welcomes_mobile_nuisance_calls_opt_out_full_release|title=MP welcomes mobile nuisance calls opt out \u2013 Yasmin Qureshi MP|date=28 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180228041307/http://www.yasminqureshi.org.uk/mp_welcomes_mobile_nuisance_calls_opt_out_full_release|archive-date=28 February 2018}}</ref> and questioning the pace of government cuts and the effect this is having on crime and local communities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15917908.mp-writes-to-home-secretary-about-rising-crime-concerns/|title=MP writes to Home Secretary about rising crime concerns|website=The Bolton News|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072855/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/15917908.mp-writes-to-home-secretary-about-rising-crime-concerns/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Parliamentary Groups==\n\nShe is currently involved with a number of All Party Parliamentary Groups ([[All-party parliamentary group|APPG]]).\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! APPG !! Role\n|-\n| India || Treasurer\n|-\n| Pakistan || Secretary\n|-\n| Palestine || Vice Chair\n|-\n| Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus || Chair and Registered Contact\n|-\n| Chess || Chair & Registered Contact\n|-\n| Childcare and Early Education || Officer\n|-\n| Communities Engagement || Secretary\n|-\n| Dalit || Chair & Registered Contact\n|-\n| Dentistry and Oral Health || Vice Chair\n|-\n| Domestic Abuse || Vice Chair\n|-\n| Greater Manchester || Treasurer\n|-\n| Hajj and Umrah || Chair & Registered Contact\n|-\n| Hormone Pregnancy Tests || Chair & Registered Contact\n|-\n| Kidney || Vice Chair<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/190213/register-190213.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=25 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072842/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/190213/register-190213.pdf |archive-date=7 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n'''APPG for Srebenica''':<ref name=\"publications.parliament.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/170329/srebrenica.htm|title=House of Commons \u2013 Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 29 March 2017: Srebrenica|website=publications.parliament.uk|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180227213740/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/170329/srebrenica.htm|archive-date=27 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Qureshi chairs this group. It seeks to \"increase awareness of the Srebrenica genocide and institutionalise 11 July in the UK as Srebrenica Memorial Day in line with the 2009 resolution of the European Parliament as the best means of honouring the victims, sending a clear message to future generations and stressing the importance of reconciliation as part of the European integration process\".<ref name=\"publications.parliament.uk\"/>\n\n'''APPG for Religion in the Media''' :\nQureshi set up and chairs this APPG. It aims to open dialogues about depictions of religion in the media, in the hope of \"fostering a better understanding and representation of religion in the media as religion is a prime motivator of individuals and the community\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160721/religion-in-the-media.htm|title=House of Commons \u2013 Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 21 July 2016: Religion in the Media|website=publications.parliament.uk|access-date=27 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160721/religion-in-the-media.htm|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n'''APPG for Chess''':\nQureshi chairs this group, which seeks to \"publicise, promote and seek support for Chess\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160203/chess.htm|title=House of Commons \u2013 Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 3 February 2016: Chess|website=publications.parliament.uk|access-date=7 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072846/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160203/chess.htm|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Based on the findings that playing chess helps improve children's concentration and focus, the APPG seeks to have chess recognised as a sport and expand the opportunities for primary and secondary school students to play chess.\n\n'''APPG on Hormone Pregnancy Tests''':\nQureshi chairs this APPG and is its point of contact. It seeks to investigate the adverse effects of Primodos (please see sub-section above).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160203/oral-hormone-pregnancy-tests.htm|title=House of Commons \u2013 Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 3 February 2016: Oral Hormone Pregnancy Tests|website=publications.parliament.uk|access-date=7 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/160203/oral-hormone-pregnancy-tests.htm|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n'''APPG for Dentistry and Oral Health''':\nQureshi is the Vice-Chair of this APPG. It acts as a \"forum for dental and oral health issues in Parliament, and works to raise the profile of dentistry, highlighting the views of both patients and the profession\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appgdentistry.org/|title=APPG Dentistry & Oral Health \u2013 Home|website=www.appgdentistry.org|access-date=7 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407074349/http://www.appgdentistry.org/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appgdentistry.org/Membership|title=APPG Dentistry & Oral Health \u2013 Membership|website=www.appgdentistry.org|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072854/http://www.appgdentistry.org/Membership|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2019 she wrote to Health Secretary Matt Hancock urging him to act to deal with what she described as a 'crisis in dentistry'.<ref name=\"dentistry.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dentistry.co.uk/2019/02/12/yasmin-qureshi-mp-urges-government-action-nhs-dentistry/|title=Yasmin Qureshi MP urges government for action on NHS dentistry|date=12 February 2019|via=www.dentistry.co.uk|access-date=25 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://www.dentistry.co.uk/2019/02/12/yasmin-qureshi-mp-urges-government-action-nhs-dentistry/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The letter was co-signed by 16 other Labour MPs.<ref name=\"dentistry.co.uk\"/>\n\n==Political positions==\n\n===Court building sales===\n\nQureshi has been a stringent critic of the widespread closure of courts and sales of court buildings throughout her time as an MP. She argues that doing so without due process and in a rushed manner \"piles yet more pressure on the remaining courts and risks hearings being further delayed and rescheduled\", with the impact of \"distressing victims and witnesses, many of whom are now forced to travel much greater distances\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://labourlist.org/2018/06/yasmin-qureshi-our-justice-system-is-being-brought-to-its-knees-by-tory-cuts/|title=Yasmin Qureshi: Our justice system is being brought to its knees by Tory cuts|date=21 June 2018|accessdate=26 February 2019|first=Yasmin|last=Qureshi|website=LabourList.org|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404225520/https://labourlist.org/2018/06/yasmin-qureshi-our-justice-system-is-being-brought-to-its-knees-by-tory-cuts/|archive-date=4 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Prison system===\n\nQureshi has been a consistent critique of the Conservatives running of the prison system. In the Huffington Post she argued that the 14% rate of prison officers leaving after a year, the record rates of prisoner suicides and the increasing safety crisis as noted by inspections indicate that prison funding and staff numbers had been cut too rapidly.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/yasmin-qureshi/prison-suicide-rates_b_13283674.html|title=Record Suicide Figures Prove That, Under This Government, The Prison System Is Broken|date=28 November 2016|website=HuffPost UK|access-date=17 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180717154246/https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/yasmin-qureshi/prison-suicide-rates_b_13283674.html|archive-date=17 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Syrian bombing===\n\nQureshi was strongly against the dropping of bombs in [[Syria]]; after travelling on a fact-finding mission with the Foreign Affairs Committee, she argued that while the bombs would certainly cause \"many innocent civilian deaths\", the evidence that the strikes would significantly weaken ISIS was unclear.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14118859.bolton-mp-yasmin-qureshi-makes-final-bid-to-prevent-uk-from-bombing-syria-during-house-of-commons-debate/|title=Bolton MP Yasmin Qureshi makes final bid to prevent UK from bombing Syria during House of Commons debate|website=The Bolton News|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072903/https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/14118859.bolton-mp-yasmin-qureshi-makes-final-bid-to-prevent-uk-from-bombing-syria-during-house-of-commons-debate/|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-34987921|title=Syria strikes: Find out how your MP voted|date=3 December 2015|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416185933/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-34987921|archive-date=16 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\nIn January 2013 and 2015, Qureshi was nominated for the Politician of the Year award at the [[British Muslim Awards]].<ref name=\"asianimage1\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/10197507.Winners_honoured_at_British_Muslim_Awards/|title=Winners honoured at British Muslim Awards|work=|location=|publisher=Asian Image|date=31 January 2013|accessdate=1 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151121173521/http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/10197507.Winners_honoured_at_British_Muslim_Awards/|archive-date=21 November 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"asianimage3\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/business/11745550.British_Muslim_Awards_2015_finalists_unveiled/|title=British Muslim Awards 2015 finalists unveiled|work=|location=|publisher=Asian Image|date=23 January 2015|accessdate=1 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150730005602/http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/business/11745550.British_Muslim_Awards_2015_finalists_unveiled/|archive-date=30 July 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2014, she was awarded the Politician of the Year award at the British Muslim Awards.<ref name=\"asianimage2\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/united_kingdom/10978079.British_Muslim_Awards_2014_winners/|title=British Muslim Awards 2014 winners|work=|location=|publisher=Asian Image|date=31 January 2014|accessdate=1 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151122185051/http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/united_kingdom/10978079.British_Muslim_Awards_2014_winners/|archive-date=22 November 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Other activities==\nIn February 2014, during a parliamentary debate on the Palestine crisis, she said of the persecution of Jewish people in [[the Holocaust]]: \"Their properties, homes, and land\u2014everything\u2014were taken away, and they were deprived of rights. Of course, many millions perished\", before going on to say that \"It is quite strange that some of the people who are running the state of Israel seem to be quite complacent and happy to allow the same to happen in Gaza\". In response, Karen Pollock of the [[Holocaust Educational Trust]] said: \"We expect our politicians to speak responsibly and sensitively about the past and about events today. These lazy and deliberate distortions have no place in British politics\". Qureshi apologised to any who were offended by her words, and stated that \"the debate was about the plight of the Palestinian people, and in no way did I mean to equate events in Gaza with the Holocaust\", adding that \"I know the Holocaust was the most brutal act of genocide of the 20th century, and no one should seek to underestimate its impact\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/feb/07/labour-mp-apologises-holocaust-remark|title=Labour MP apologises for Holocaust remark|work=The Guardian|agency=Press Association|date=7 February 2014|accessdate=10 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317171354/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/feb/07/labour-mp-apologises-holocaust-remark|archive-date=17 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Dysch|first=Marcus|url=http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/115505/labour-mp-yasmin-qureshi-apologises-gaza-holocaust-comparison|title=Labour MP Yasmin Qureshi apologises for Gaza-Holocaust comparison|work=The Jewish Chronicle|date=10 February 2014|accessdate=10 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011065610/http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/115505/labour-mp-yasmin-qureshi-apologises-gaza-holocaust-comparison|archive-date=11 October 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/feb/07/labour-mp-apologises-holocaust-remark|title=Labour MP apologises for Holocaust remark|first=Press|last=Association|date=7 February 2014|via=www.theguardian.com|access-date=10 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317171354/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/feb/07/labour-mp-apologises-holocaust-remark|archive-date=17 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, Qureshi opposed mandatory labelling of meat coming from animals killed by [[Dhabihah|halal]] and [[Shechita|kosher]] methods. She drew attention to studies which indicated that halal methods of slaughtering may not be more painful than stunning, saying \"a myth is being perpetuated that somehow kosher and halal methods, carried out as they should be, are more painful and cause more suffering to the animal, but that is incorrect\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.politics.co.uk/news/2014/05/14/mps-block-compulsory-halal-meat-labelling |title=MPs block compulsory halal meat labelling |publisher=politics.co.uk |first=Adam |last=Bienkov |date=14 May 2014 |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707201144/http://www.politics.co.uk/news/2014/05/14/mps-block-compulsory-halal-meat-labelling |archive-date=7 July 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2014-05-13a.654.0 |title=Right to supply tickets to events of national significance |publisher=TheyWorkForYou |date=13 May 2014 |accessdate=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808150050/http://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2014-05-13a.654.0 |archive-date=8 August 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, ''[[The Times]]'' stated that Qureshi accepted a \u00a35,000 donation from [[Sufyan Ismail]] but failed to declare it;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/extremist-leads-muslim-lobby-group-7q2hg30zc|title=Extremist leads Muslim lobby group|first=Dominic Kennedy|last=Investigations\u00a0Editor|date=10 April 2017|publisher=|via=www.thetimes.co.uk|access-date=7 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407072843/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/extremist-leads-muslim-lobby-group-7q2hg30zc|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> it was found that the donation was in fact declared on time and in keeping with parliamentary procedure, it was declared through Ismail's company name 'One Group' and can be found on public parliamentary donation records.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmregmem/150713/150713.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=17 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121030125/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmregmem/150713/150713.pdf |archive-date=21 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Qureshi was banned from driving for 6 months for driving without insurance and using a mobile phone, whilst already having 9 points.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-manchester-11027669|title=Bolton MP is banned from driving|date=19 August 2010|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416181332/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-manchester-11027669|archive-date=16 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://yasminqureshi.org.uk/ Yasmin Qureshi MP] Official constituency website\n*{{UK MP links | parliament = yasmin-qureshi/3924 | guardian = 8667/yasmin-qureshi | publicwhip = Yasmin_Qureshi | theywork = yasmin_qureshi | record = Yasmin-Qureshi/Bolton-South-East/1150 | bbc = 35869.stm | journalisted = }}\n* {{C-SPAN|yasminqureshi}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|uk}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Brian Iddon]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|[[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]] for [[Bolton South East (UK Parliament constituency)|Bolton South East]]}}|years=[[2010 United Kingdom general election|2010]]\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{North West Labour Party MPs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Qureshi, Yasmin}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of London South Bank University]]\n[[Category:British politicians of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:British Muslims]]\n[[Category:Female members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Labour Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Pakistani emigrants to the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Naturalised citizens of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:British people of Punjabi descent]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2010\u20132015]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2015\u20132017]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2017\u20132019]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2019\u2013]]\n[[Category:21st-century British women politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for Bolton South East]]\n", "name_user": "Sobi2203", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:Karl Turner\u2192Karl Turner (British politician)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yasmin_Qureshi"}
{"title_page": "I-formation (tennis)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{citation style|date=March 2017}}\n{{Underlinked|date=April 2017}}\n}}\n'''I-formation''' is a [[doubles tennis]] strategy carefully planned to confuse the opponent returning the [[Serve (tennis)|serve]]. \"The name comes from its resemblance to American football's [[I formation]], in which the [[Fullback (gridiron football)|fullback]] positions right behind the [[Halfback (American football)|halfback]], who positions right behind the [[quarterback]].\"<ref>(krajco \"n.d.\") http://www.tennisserver.com/wildcards/wildcards_02_10.html</ref>\n\n.<ref>\"The net player on the serving team crouches down (so they don't get hit by the serve.) On the centre service line. The server hits the serve from directly behind her on the baseline\".</ref>  The net player then indicates, (privately); typically with their hands behind their back which side of the court they will move to as the return of serve is hit. These hand gestures let the server at the baseline know which side of the court they are to serve to, and than move to. For intermediate players such as league, or club players it is recommended that the server head to the opposite side to which the net player is headed so that maximum court coverage is obtained) Advanced competitors such as professional; and tour players are known to use other combinations for example [[Tennis strategy|Australian Doubles]] which deliberately exposes one side of the court to entice the return of serve be hit into the open space.\n\nThe ultimate aim here is for the net player to cut off the return of serve hopefully ending the point.\n\n==Why I-formation is Effective==\nIn [[tennis]] you want to keep the ball away from the net player, because it is easy to put the ball away from closer to the net than any other position on the court.\n\nThis tactic has the player returning the serve guess as to which side the opponents net player will be. So basically there is a 50\u201350 chance the person returning the server is going to hit the ball right into their opponents net player which effectively can be the worst place to return the serve in doubles.\n\n==Tips==\nTo play this tactic successfully It's important players be comfortable serving the ball with enough precision to place the ball out wide, into the body; and down the \"T\" in each service box. Accuracy is also required so you don't hit the net-player in the back or head.\n\nAnother key to success with this tactic is understanding the ins and outs of returning a serve, and what is involved when choosing to hit down the line as opposed to a crosscourt return. For example, it is harder to change the direction of the ball when it is travelling quickly. Also, there is a higher margin of error when hitting the ball crosscourt, because the distance between the net and the baseline is longer and the net is lower in the centre where the ball path crosses the net.\n\nIt helps to know your opponent's weaknesses and strengths before playing this strategy; so if your opponent has a whopping big crosscourt return of serve,  this is good to know beforehand; because you can force them to return the ball down the line where the net is higher, the distance is shorter and the angle is harder; this  can [[Intimidation|intimidating]] the player returning the serve into making an error.\n\nThe net-player is required to get low, and it is important that they be able to move quickly out of this position, so it's recommended the net player be on their feet, crouching, as opposed to one or both knees. Also, it is easier to move to the ball from the balls of the feet as opposed to being flat-footed. Also typically you want this position to be uncomfortable because you are going to want to move out of it quickly.\n\n==Communicating to the Server==\n\nOften the net player will put their hands behind the back to indicate where the server should serve. So if the server is serving on the deuce side of the court the index finger is used to point to the ad side, The middle finger is used to indicate a to-the-body shot, and the pinkie finger is used to reflect the down-the-line position.<ref>(Westermann 2015) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NXoOGJkBIuQ</ref> The net-player then communicates if they are going to move to the ad or deuce service-box. It's also common for the net-player to walk back to the service line and whisper his/her choice of combinations to the server; this helps to slow the game down, which can frustrate the returning team's [[rhythm]]; and also helps the server to stay calm.\n\n==References==\n\nAntoun, A. (2007) ''Women's Tennis Tactics'', United States of America, Human Kinetics.\n\nKrajco, K. (\"n.d.\") ''The I-Formation: Variation of Australian Doubles'' retrieved 19 March 2017 from http://www.tennisserver.com/wildcards/wildcards_02_10.html\n\nWestermann, I.  Aug 14 2015. ''Using Hand Signals in Doubles - Ask Ian #49. EssentialTennis''. Retrieved on 22 March 2017 from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NXoOGJkBIuQ\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Tennis shots]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{citation style|date=March 2017}}\n{{Underlinked|date=April 2017}}\n}}\n'''I-formation''' is a [[doubles tennis]] strategy carefully planned to confuse the opponent returning the [[Serve (tennis)|serve]]. \"The name comes from its resemblance to American football's [[I formation]], in which the fullback positions right behind the halfback, who positions right behind the quarterback.\"<ref>(krajco \"n.d.\") http://www.tennisserver.com/wildcards/wildcards_02_10.html</ref>\n\n.<ref>\"The net player on the serving team crouches down (so they don't get hit by the serve.) On the centre service line. The server hits the serve from directly behind her on the baseline\".</ref>  The net player then indicates, (privately); typically with their hands behind their back which side of the court they will move to as the return of serve is hit. These hand gestures let the server at the baseline know which side of the court they are to serve to, and than move to. For intermediate players such as league, or club players it is recommended that the server head to the opposite side to which the net player is headed so that maximum court coverage is obtained) Advanced competitors such as professional; and tour players are known to use other combinations for example [[Tennis strategy|Australian Doubles]] which deliberately exposes one side of the court to entice the return of serve be hit into the open space.\n\nThe ultimate aim here is for the net player to cut off the return of serve hopefully ending the point.\n\n==Why I-formation is Effective==\nIn tennis you want to keep the ball away from the net player, because it is easy to put the ball away from closer to the net than any other position on the court.\n\nThis tactic has the player returning the serve guess as to which side the opponents net player will be. So basically there is a 50\u201350 chance the person returning the server is going to hit the ball right into their opponents net player which effectively can be the worst place to return the serve in doubles.\n\n==Tips==\nTo play this tactic successfully It's important players be comfortable serving the ball with enough precision to place the ball out wide, into the body; and down the \"T\" in each service box. Accuracy is also required so you don't hit the net-player in the back or head.\n\nAnother key to success with this tactic is understanding the ins and outs of returning a serve, and what is involved when choosing to hit down the line as opposed to a crosscourt return. For example, it is harder to change the direction of the ball when it is travelling quickly. Also, there is a higher margin of error when hitting the ball crosscourt, because the distance between the net and the baseline is longer and the net is lower in the centre where the ball path crosses the net.\n\nIt helps to know your opponent's weaknesses and strengths before playing this strategy; so if your opponent has a whopping big crosscourt return of serve,  this is good to know beforehand; because you can force them to return the ball down the line where the net is higher, the distance is shorter and the angle is harder; this  can [[Intimidation|intimidating]] the player returning the serve into making an error.\n\nThe net-player is required to get low, and it is important that they be able to move quickly out of this position, so it's recommended the net player be on their feet, crouching, as opposed to one or both knees. Also, it is easier to move to the ball from the balls of the feet as opposed to being flat-footed. Also typically you want this position to be uncomfortable because you are going to want to move out of it quickly.\n\n==Communicating to the Server==\n\nOften the net player will put their hands behind the back to indicate where the server should serve. So if the server is serving on the deuce side of the court the index finger is used to point to the ad side, The middle finger is used to indicate a to-the-body shot, and the pinkie finger is used to reflect the down-the-line position.<ref>(Westermann 2015) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NXoOGJkBIuQ</ref> The net-player then communicates if they are going to move to the ad or deuce service-box. It's also common for the net-player to walk back to the service line and whisper his/her choice of combinations to the server; this helps to slow the game down, which can frustrate the returning team's [[rhythm]]; and also helps the server to stay calm.\n\n==References==\n\nAntoun, A. (2007) ''Women's Tennis Tactics'', United States of America, Human Kinetics.\n\nKrajco, K. (\"n.d.\") ''The I-Formation: Variation of Australian Doubles'' retrieved 19 March 2017 from http://www.tennisserver.com/wildcards/wildcards_02_10.html\n\nWestermann, I.  Aug 14 2015. ''Using Hand Signals in Doubles - Ask Ian #49. EssentialTennis''. Retrieved on 22 March 2017 from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NXoOGJkBIuQ\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Tennis shots]]\n", "name_user": "Wafflyjar", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added Wikilinks", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I-formation_(tennis)"}
